text:
🌸 TIRTIR Mask Fit All Cover Pink Cushion - This gem has SPF 50+ PA+++ for sun protection! It’s lighter than the regular TIRTIR Red Cushion Foundation, but it still does wonders for my uneven complexion. Total must-have! ☀️

🌟 tfit Translucent Set Finishing Powder in Pink - This powder blurs my pores and keeps my skin matte while controlling sebum. I do wish the puff was a bit bigger and softer for easier application, but it’s still a game-changer! Just requires a little extra love. 💖

🎨 rom&nd Twinkle Pen Liner in 05 Sunset Hazel and 02 Golden Wave - I’m obsessed! I use Sunset Hazel for my eyeliner (it’s the perfect brown with a hint of red) and Golden Wave as a subtle liquid eyeshadow. I paired with the rom&nd Better Than Palette Eyeshadow Palette #00 Light & Glitter Garden for a natural, shimmery look! 🌈

💖 For lashes, I swear by Maybelline Sky High Mascara and the Shiseido Eyelash Curler. This duo is my holy grail! The mascara is waterproof but comes off easily with cleansing oil, and the curler? Just perfect for my eye shape! 😍

💦 Lastly, I spritz the MIGUHARA Vital Shine Mist Serum all over for that hydration boost. It feels amazing!

💬 I’d love to hear about your makeup routines! What are your go-to products? Let’s chat in the comments! 👇

text:
✨ Say goodbye to dry patches for good! ✨ My first impression of Purito SEOUL Wonder Releaf Centella Cream 🥰

I’ve received my first PR gift 👏👏👏 from YesStyle and I am excited to share my thoughts on using this amazing face cream - Purito SEOUL Wonder Releaf Centella Cream. It is packed with K-Beauty staples like Cica, Squalane, and Ceramide NP for calming, moisturizing, and barrier-supporting care. It is vegan-friendly and the clinically tested formula is perfect for sensitive skin.

😇 I do not have problems with sensitive skin so I am a bit worried that the moisturizer may be too rich for my combination skin. To my surprise, my skin loves it 💖! The texture is luxurious and easy to spread on my face. The cream is rich yet lightweight so it creates a silky skin barrier without feeling greasy. No dry patches, no flaky skin, and no skin tightness 😊😊😊

I love the scent of the cream too! It is my beloved Lavender 🌿 ! I know some of you gals prefer unscented products (Purito SEOUL got an unscented version 🥰) but the extra kick of the essential oil soothes my nerves so well. I’ll fold my hands, cover my face, and take a deep breath when I use this cream in the evening. It helps me to unwind the stress and tension during the day🧘‍♀️

✨ Tips for using this cream:

1️⃣ After applying this cream, wait a minute till it is absorbed. Then, apply sunscreen as usual.

2️⃣ I will suggest using a sponge to press the foundation on the face instead of blending it after using Purito SEOUL Wonder Releaf Centella Cream. The foundation stays on my skin perfectly and this method won’t wipe out the protective layers of the cream.

3️⃣ If you have very sensitive skin and prefer something unscented, check out Purito SEOUL Wonder Releaf Centella Cream Unscented which has a similar formula for hypersensitive skin.

Have you tried any Purito SEOUL products? Share your thoughts below 👇

text:
Quick try-on of the Em Cosmetics Lip Mage Tinted Serums!

(Btw I apologize for the inconsistent lighting in this reel, I just figured out a solution today.)

The website says: “A youth enhancing water-based formula that delivers a long lasting stain plus sheer, buildable color, for naturally defined, plump & juicy lips.”

Texture:
These are one of the most comfortable lip stains I’ve tried. They have a hydrating, gel-like formula with a little bit of a cushiony feel that’s really nice on the lips. If I had to compare them to a similar K-Beauty product I’d say the Romand dewyful water tint comes close because they both feel ultra comfortable and non-drying.

Scent:
I detect a slight caramel smell but it’s so subtle I honestly don’t even know if I’m making that up.

Colors:
K-Beauty lip stains are usually super bright, so I like that Em launched a line of stains that are a bit different from what I usually see. They’re more muted and easy to wear. My favorite is enigma, which is a warm rose. I think the crowd favorite will be mirage, a slightly cool toned brown. Definitely a color I haven’t seen in a stain before!

Stain:
The only negative aspect I can think of is that the stain isn’t the most even I’ve tried. When I wipe these off, I notice a little patchiness on my lips that I don’t usually experience with my favorite stains. That said, it’s pretty subtle, but I did want to mention it.

Price:
These are $22 at Em Cosmetics and you can get 15% of with my code EM_STATEOFKAIT: https://rstyle.me/+w4ocQNjorfurQTPgdAia2w

This is my favorite out of the trio! Its lightweight, gel-watery texture calms and soothes without adding extra burden to my combination skin. Perfect for reducing redness and irritation while refining skin texture!

2️⃣ What is Mighty Bamboo Panthenol Cream?
✨ Infused with 100,000 ppm Panthenol and Korean Bamboo, this cream repairs and hydrates your skin barrier like a pro.
🔒 Locks in moisture for that radiant, dewy glow.

💚 My Experience:
This cream has a milky shade and gel-creamy texture that’s slightly thicker, making it perfect for combination to dry and dry skin. It locks in moisture and repairs the skin barrier, leaving a radiant, dewy glow.

3️⃣ What is Oat-In Calming Gel Cream?
💧 Powered by Avena Sativa (Oat) and Panthenol, it nourishes, hydrates, and calms dry, sensitive skin.
🌬️ Lightweight gel absorbs in seconds, delivering hydration deep within.
✨ Perfect for layering after your favorite serum!

💚 My Experience:
With its refreshing gel texture and slight cooling sensation, it’s ideal for combination and oily skin during Winter. It absorbs quickly, hydrates deeply, and leaves my skin glowing without any tingling or dryness.

Definitely yes! This trio is perfect for calming, softening, and rehydrating the skin. They are fragrance-free and help soften my rough skin texture without interfering with makeup applied afterward. These products work beautifully with active ingredients like Vitamin C, Retinol, or Tretinoin. 🥰

text:
🥰 🌾 Hydrating Serum with Rice Power - I’m from Rice Serum

I am glad that I can finally try I’m from Rice Serum 😍 I heard a lot of good things about this brand and their hero products, Rice Toner (check my last post for the product review) , Rice Serum and Rice Cream so I am excited to try them.

I am a sucker for face serum and this product works beautifully on my normal to dry skin. I love the milky texture of the serum, which is in between toner and milky emulsion, not too light and not too heavy which is great for all skin types. ☺️

I can feel that my skin is super hydrated after using the Rice Toner and Rice Serum. Both products give me a natural radiance without feeling greasy and I will use sunscreen after the products are absorbed to make sure my makeup stays in place. 😘

So what is I’m from Rice Serum?
It is a serum infused with 🌾 73% Rice Germ Fermented Extract from Rice Buds, blended with Niacinamide and Hyaluronic Acid.

So what are these ingredients for?

1️⃣ Promoting healthy skin, restoring skin radiance, and revitalizing dull skin complexion.
2️⃣ Providing deep moisturization.
3️⃣ With 73% Rice Germ Fermented Extract (retains over 65% of rice’s nutritional value), it helps to promote collagen production and improve skin elasticity.

I did worry about the texture when I first spotted it online as it looks a bit heavy but actually, It is weightless and refreshing! It is viscous when I apply it to my skin but it spreads out and is absorbed easily which leaves a sheen, silky, almost glowy finish to my skin. ✨

I use it with I’m from Rice Toner twice a day and I’m from Rice Cream at night. I love how hydrating these products offer and my normal to dry skin simply loves them 🥰.

Have you tried I’m from Rice Serum?

text:
🚨I made this reel purely for the hair … but also to share with you a little backstory. 

Our brand @dr.idriss had a booth yesterday at a conference that @sephora hosts for all their managers. It was a very overwhelming experience planning for it over the last few months, as we are one of the smallest brands they have in stores. And to make it even more intimidating, we were setting up alongside the plethora of multimillion dollar brands they have. 

Being fully self-funded (and in the process of funding clinical studies for R&D), can we say “err…on a budget” 🙋‍♀️ we had to work with what we have, and what we have was us 💪 

Standing out in an explosion of candy and hi-def color (and hair volume) we managed to distract and attract and had so much fun doing the damn thing💥 

Moral of this story: No matter the roadblocks, no matter the cost, when you can’t invest in things, always always always… invest in the people and yourselves 💜

A special thank you to this incredible lady @dima_osko for bringing the glam, the volume and my beach waves to life 🔥

text:
⭐️ Beauty of Joseon Revive Eye Serum vs Some By Mi Retinol Intense Eye Cream 👀

❤️ Get these eye creams at YesStyle or Olive Young Global. Enter my code BEAUTYKAT321 to save more. ♥️

🧐 Traditional Retinol Eye Cream - Some By Mi Retinol Intense Eye Cream contains 0.1% Retinol to target skin pigmentation and wrinkles. Retinol is the gold standard of anti-aging skincare – a vitamin A derivative that boosts collagen production and evens skin tone for a radiant complexion.

👀 I bought this eye cream about three months ago, and Some By Mi recently launched a new packaging for this product. Both the old and new versions incorporate Niacinamide for skin brightening, as well as Hyaluronic Acid and Panthenol for intense hydration.

What do I think about Some By Mi?

It glides easily onto the skin, and I love its creamy, luxurious texture. It rehydrates 💦 my under-eye areas so well and gives me a healthy glow right away. ⭐️

I noticed some improvements in my fine lines after using it for 3-4 weeks but the result is subtle. 😅

🔌 Meet the Powerhouse Cousin of Retinol - Beauty of Joseon Revive Eye Serum contains 2% Retinal Liposome which incorporates natural lipids and oils, plus an active ingredient, 0.02% Retinal.

Retinal is converted directly to Retinoic Acid, which works faster and more effectively on the skin than Retinol.

What do I think about Beauty of Joseon?

I’ve been using it for almost a year, and I am in love with it. 🍦 The texture is creamy but lightweight, so it absorbs into the skin quickly.

However, it’s not rich enough for my under-eye areas if I use it in winter. I have to apply a serum before using this product, but I don’t need to when using Some By Mi.

I noticed moisturizing results after two weeks – my fine lines improved, and my skin became smoother and firmer. However, after a while, I didn’t see as significant a difference as I used to. 😅

💕 In short, I recommend both products:

❄️ Some By Mi Retinol Intense Eye Cream for dry and wrinkled skin;

✅ and Beauty of Joseon Revive Eye Serum for all skin types.

What would you choose?

text:
Milani sent me their Cheek Kiss Cream Bronzer and Blushes!

The bronzer in Hey Honey is a very warm-toned shade with a hard-pressed cream formula that’s slightly emollient to help with the blend ability. I found it lasted on my face for several hours without fading, my only issue is that the color is a bit too orange on my cool skin. I’d really like to see a shade expansion in this line!

The blush in Blushing Berry is a gorgeous, bright cherry red with a more dewy formula than the bronzer. This faded from my face in about 20 minutes, so it’s unfortunately not worth keeping to me. My face eats cream blush so I tend to prefer matte liquid or cream formulas that adhere to my skin better. But if you don’t have that issue, I think this is a beautiful, affordable product.

The blush is $10.99 and the bronzer is $12.99 at Ultra.

text:
How I Tackled Sebum & Blemishes Without the Pain ~ Mediheal 💧

Gifted by @mediheal_us and @bazzaal_

✨ What is Mediheal Madecassoside Blemish Pad? ✨
The Mediheal Madecassoside Blemish Pad is a soothing toner pad designed to calm and reduce the appearance of blemishes and dark spots on uneven, post-acne skin. Made with vegan fibers and enriched with Centella Asiatica and micro-particle Madecassoside, it helps keep your skin soft, hydrated, and nourished while improving skin tone and texture. These hypoallergenic pads are suitable for all skin types, including sensitive and acne-prone skin 🌿.

How to Use?
After cleansing, gently wipe the pad across your face to tone, moisturize, and prep your skin for day or night. You can also leave the pads on targeted areas like your forehead, cheeks, or chin for a quick, intensive skin fix! For extra hydration, use the pads as a mini sheet mask. 💦.

✨ My Experience with Mediheal Madecassoside Blemish Pad ✨

I love the soothing, calming, and hydrating effects of this blemish pad 😍. Despite not storing it in the fridge, it gives me a subtle cooling sensation after cleansing ❄️. I gently wipe my skin with the pad and often use it as a mini mask for rehydration. The square design is a game-changer — it stays perfectly on my skin, and I can even fold it to cover my nose!

Tip: After using the pad, my skin becomes soft and hydrated, which makes it easier to draw out sebaceous filaments (excess sebum) on my nose and prevent blackheads. I simply wrap my index finger with the pad (thanks to the vegan fibers, which aren’t too soft nor too stiff), then gently press and push on my nose 👃. The sebum sticks to the pad, which is much more effective and painless than using a stainless steel blemish remover 💥. Remember to use the pad at least once daily to keep the oiliness at bay!

If you’re like me and prefer gentle solutions, this pad is a great way to manage oiliness without causing redness or irritation. It’s versatile, convenient, and gentle enough for daily use. Will you try it? 🩷

text:
What people say VS What I hear as a skinfluencer

1. "Skincare stings and burns🔥"
 Me: damaged skin barrier. When your skin barrier is weak or damaged it's not doing it's job to protect the skin and keep the bad things from getting deep into the skin. This vulnerability means that skincare that worked fine on your healthy skin, can all of sudden cause irritation on skin with a weak barrier.

2. "My skin is so oily 😓" 
Me: dehydrated skin. Dehydrated skin is skin that lacks WATER, not moisture. It's a myth that only dry skin folks experience dehydrated skin symptoms. In fact, it's common that skin will overproduce oil to compensate for the dehydration. So if you're noticing more oil suddenly, consider your skin might be dehydrated.

3. "I have itchy rough skin" 
Me: eczema🤔 Not a diagnosis, but it might be a good idea to explore the possibility with a medical professional. Especially if that dry, itch patch of skin is red, oozing or painful. Eczema can be very common in cold and dry climates and can be fairly easy to manage if you know what you're dealing with!

text:
Milk Makeup launced four new shades of their odyssey up oil glosses.

Price: $26
Scent: sweet vanilla scent (although it smells a bit like creamsicles to me!)
Description: A non-sticky, hydrating lip gloss made with vitamin-rich oils for juicy, semi-sheer color with a long-lasting high-shine finish.

Texture:
They’re marketed as a cross between a lip oil and a lip gloss, meaning they are more lightweight and less sticky than traditional glosses. To me, these are quite thin, but they do a have a tiny amount of grip, meaning they don’t slip around too badly, but they’re just not cushiony or smoothing in the way I usually like lip gloss to be. I’d almost describe them as a cross between a lip oil and a lip serum because they’re thin, buttery, and lightweight.

What I LOVE about these is the way my lips feel when they wear off. My lips feel super soft and hydrated, and like there’s a bit of an oil left behind. I definitely agree with the claims that it’s a hydrating gloss!

These would be best suited for someone who wants a lightweight lip oil that barely feels like anything on the lips and leaves behind a hydrated feeling. 🤟🏻

Link to Odyssey Glosses at Sephora: https://rstyle.me/+w1umFj67E19ldKDP7PJzZw (aff)

text:
✨ For Fans of Centella Asiatica Extract: Meet THE PLANT BASE AC Clear Moisture Cica Cream! ✨

YesStyle Code: BEAUTYKAT321

This cream contains 76% Centella Asiatica, providing refreshing moisture for combination skin affected by environmental damage.

Centella Asiatica Extract is known for soothing dry, red, irritated, or inflamed skin. It has been used for thousands of years in India as an anti-aging remedy. 🌟

But that’s not all! This cream also features:

🍵 Green Tea Powder - Rich in vitamins A and C to protect and keep your skin healthy.

🌿 Tea Tree - Known for its potent sterilizing effects, 12 times stronger than other plants.

My Experience:
If you’ve seen my previous post, you know that I’ve been dealing with acne on my jawline, possibly due to hormonal changes. This cream has been a lifesaver, and thanks to The Plant Base for sending me several products to try. So far, I love using it alongside my other skincare products. Here’s my routine:

☀️ AM:
1) After cleansing and toning, I apply a spot treatment with 5.5% Benzoyl Peroxide.
2) Apply The Plant Base AC Clear Cica Gel (72% Centella Asiatica) to my cheek area to reduce redness.
3) Apply The Plant Base AC Clear Moisture Cica Cream to my face and neck.
4) Finish with sunscreen.

🌙 PM:
1) Same as AM routine.
2) Apply The Plant Base Waterfall Moist Balanced Hyaluronic Acid.
3) Apply The Plant Base AC Clear Moisture Cica Cream.

🍀 When using the Cica Gel and Cica Cream, apply them in thin layers to avoid any white, rubbery residues on your hairline.

⚠️ For those with dry & sensitive skin, you might skip the Cica Gel (NOT the cream) which contains alcohol, and use The Plant Base Waterfall Moist Balanced Hyaluronic Acid instead.

The Plant Base AC Clear Moisture Cica Cream has a subtle herbal scent due to essential oils, which doesn’t irritate my eyes, though it gives a brief tingling sensation that disappears quickly. I can even use the Cica Cream under my eyes.

My skin feels well-hydrated and calm, with reduced redness and improved acne. I do feel a bit oily in the morning, but Hong Kong’s humid weather contributes to that.

Have you tried The Plant Base? What do you think about it?

text:
💕 Daily Gentle Cleanser with Salicylic Acid - Even my dehydrated skin loves it 💕

YesStyle Reward Code: BEAUTYKAT321
Olive Young Coupon Code: BEAUTYKAT321

I have been using Jumiso for almost a month and I truly love the 🐌 snail essence, 🐌 snail peptide cream, and all the 🍊 Vitamin C serums. 🥰 However, I feel skeptical about Jumiso Pore-Purifying Salicylic Acid Foaming Cleanser 🫧. I don’t like face cleansers that contain AHA and Salicylic Acid (BHA) as I worry that these ingredients will dry out my dehydrated skin and irritate my eyes.

But I am wrong! 😅 Jumiso Pore-Purifying Salicylic Acid Foaming Cleanser is so gentle that I can use it daily. It contains 0.5% Salicylic Acid and Blue Clay which help to exfoliate dead skin cells to reveal radiant and glowing skin.

I like how it cleans my skin and helps me to draw the impurities on my nose. As you see in the reel, I didn’t use any gadget to remove the excess sebum on my t-zone area but this cleanser is so effective! My skin feels fresh and smooth as this low-pH cleanser gently exfoliates the skin and unclogs pores.

It also contains 🍎 Apple Fruit Extract and 🌿 Coptis Japonica Root Extract for soothing and brightening benefits while keeping the skin’s moisture level. The non-comedogenic formula is suitable for all skin types too.

The only downside of this cleanser is that, it is not designed for eye areas so I will use another face cleanser in the evening after removing my makeup.

text:
PEEKABOO—ACNE SCARS, WHERE ARE YOU? 

This patient had been dealing with deep acne scars for years, but after seeing my work on social media, she knew exactly who to trust. I'm known for my unmatched expertise in subcision, and for her, I took it a step further—customizing a multi-treatment approach to plump those scars, build collagen production and create smooth, healthy skin.

I combined subcision with Sculptra to kickstart collagen production, used Bellafill to lift and fill in the scars, and hit every layer with laser resurfacing—Halo for broad improvement and Profractional for deep remodeling. The results? INSANE. Initially, she had swelling and scabs, but within a week, they were gone—revealing fresh, baby-smooth skin. She was blown away by how much her skin transformed after just one treatment.
 
I improved those scars like bing bop boom boom boom bop bam!  

And while acne scars aren’t a one-and-done fix, this was the perfect first step toward long-term results.

💥 DON’T FORGET THE SKINCARE 💥
I set her up with a powerhouse regimen featuring the best of @emer.skin, ensuring her skin heals fast while staying hydrated, bright, and glowing. Post-treatment care is everything—because I don’t just treat scars, I transform skin.

text:
The @urbandecaycosmetics Face Bond Self-Setting Waterproof Foundation is EVERYTHING.

Website description: “Ultra-thin, medium coverage foundation with skincare benefits of a serum.”

The foundation is $40, comes in 40 shades shades, has a natural matte finish, medium-buildable coverage, ultra-thin texture, and a blurring effect. It’s waterproof, humidity proof, sweat proof, smudge and transfer resistant, and they specifically made shades for olive skin tone with their “chromium oxide green pigment.”

My thoughts:
I am extraordinarily picky about…well, everything… but especially foundation because I have sensitive, acne-prone, combination skin that gets oily in my t-zone no matter what I do.

This is the first foundation I’ve tried that keeps my skin matte while still looking like skin. It only started looking dry after 8 hours of wear, and that was on a day where I was super active and rubbing my face with a paper towel because I had to film a lot of lip swatches. I’m sure that on a normal day it would perform even better.

This might just be the best foundation for oily skin that I’ve ever tried.

Note: if you have dry skin, I would avoid this at all costs lol 

Link to Face Bond at Sephora: https://rstyle.me/+Wr8072FzhmVYjepia2OVwA

text:
Fitglow Beauty just launched their new Ceramide Hydra-Balms, a “multi-benefit hybrid lip serum + oil-in-one with peptides, ceramides + glutathione.”

They’re $28 each (but you can get 20% off with my code KAIT20) and they have a subtle vanilla scent and a cooling metal applicator.

These are 100% accurately named because the texture is super lightweight and runny, almost like a liquid. Their description of these being a serum meets an oil with a shiny finish and non-sticky feel is spot on. 

Website Description:
“Pack on luminous glossy colour while hydrating your lips with our supercharged, Ceramide, and Peptide-rich, transformative lip hydra treatment balm. Backed by the latest European plant formulation—this cooling, non-sticky lip hydra balm boosts healing, keeps lips looking youthfully supple, and defends against moisture loss and everyday damage. Barrier-protecting Triple Lipid Complex enhances lip smoothness, natural Phytosterols fight flakes, and our best-in-class Peptide Complex stimulates collagen and volume for an elevated breakthrough in lip health with an unbeatable shine.”

People have asked me to compare these to the Lip Serums and they’re different every way. The lip serums aren’t very shiny, they’re more of a liquid lip balm with a semi-thick, gel cushion. I find the Lip Serums to be more nourishing on my lips, but if you like something shinier and more lightweight, I’d go for the Hydra-Balms.

My favorites are rosewood, glowgetter, and liv! I recommend using a lip liner for some structure unless you're only applying a small amount.

*PR

Shop Ceramide Hydra-Balms at Fitglow: https://go.shopmy.us/p-7867454

text:
Please ignore my less than stellar makeup, I was testing new products and didn’t love the colors.

Anywho, the Saie dew bronze formula is great for dry skin! I LOVE the shade Salt, which looks like it would be pretty dark but the product is so sheer that it blends out easily on my light cool skin.

Unfortunately this formula fades extremely fast on me, but that’s because my face eats dewy products for lunch. My combination skin really needs base products with a natural or soft matte finish in order to last, so the Dewy Bronze will be best suited for dry skin!

If you’re loving the glossy lip trend as much as I am, you need to pair it with a perfectly matched lip liner to achieve that full, natural, and feminine pout! 💄 Here’s my secret for a quick lip transformation:

✨ Step 1: Fill your lips with a glossy lip product to give them a plump, hydrated look.

✨ Step 2: Use a lip liner with a rounded tip to define your lip shape. Slightly overline for a fuller, softer vibe—don’t forget to keep the corners rounded for a youthful finish!

Personally, I prefer applying lip gloss before lip liner because it creates a softer, more natural look without forming a harsh line along my lips. But honestly, there’s no right or wrong way—just go with what works for you! 😊

text:
💧🥰 Removing makeup while dissolving blackheads - AXIS-Y ay&me Biome Resetting Moringa Cleansing Oil ❤️

This cleansing oil from Korea really catches my eye and here are the reasons:

First, the design of the packaging is not in a typical K-Beauty style. I love how simple it is but the products still look expensive. 💵

Second, it contains 5 different prebiotics & probiotics for improving skin complexion. I will say it is a high-end, yet affordable skincare product.

🫧 So what is AXIS-Y ay&me Biome Resetting Moringa Cleansing Oil? And what does it claim to be?
AXIS-Y Made for Me By Me (ay&me) is a skincare series that AXIS-Y spent 2 years developing and this cleansing oil is one of the products from this line. It cleanses away makeup, excess sebum, whiteheads, and blackheads in ONE step so no double-cleansing is needed.

What do I think about this product?

😍 Pros:
It cleanses my makeup and dirt effectively and I just love how I feel after using it. My t-zone area feels so smooth and soft, which is like after using a peeling mask and all the blackheads are gone! I must say, it is so satisfying! 🥰

🕊️ The oil is weightless but it is still thicker than most of the cleansing oils that I’ve used. Having said that, it’s not greasy and it leaves a light hydrating finish. 💦

Talking about double-cleansing, I still use face cleanser after this cleansing oil because old habits die hard. 😅 Remember to use it on dry face and dry hands, massage your face, and add water to emulsify. Rinse thoroughly with lukewarm water.

🤨 Cons:
It has a Chinese herbal and sandalwood scent. 🪵 It doesn’t irritate my skin but I have sensitive eyes which I don’t feel very comfortable with.

📖 For the functions of the ingredients, please refer comment for details 💕

text:
*Korean Glass Skin: The Ultimate Skincare Trend*

Korean beauty (K-beauty) has taken the global beauty industry by storm, and one of its most iconic trends is the concept of "glass skin." Glass skin refers to a complexion that is incredibly smooth, luminous, and translucent, much like a piece of glass. Achieving this flawless, dewy look is the result of meticulous skincare routines designed to nourish, hydrate, and perfect the skin over time.

At the heart of glass skin is the idea of healthy, well-hydrated skin. It’s not just about masking imperfections or covering up with makeup. Instead, glass skin emphasizes the importance of achieving beauty from within, using a combination of skincare products and techniques that focus on long-term results. The goal is a clear, even-toned complexion that reflects light effortlessly, giving the face a radiant, almost ethereal glow.

The Key Components of a Glass Skin Routine

Achieving glass skin involves a comprehensive skincare regimen, with a focus on hydration, exfoliation, and protection. Here are some key steps:

1. **Double Cleansing**: The first step in the glass skin routine is the K-beauty staple of double cleansing. This process involves using an oil-based cleanser to remove makeup, sunscreen, and impurities, followed by a water-based cleanser to thoroughly clean the skin. Proper cleansing is crucial for preventing breakouts and ensuring that the skin is prepared to absorb subsequent skincare products.

2. **Exfoliation**: Regular exfoliation helps remove dead skin cells, promoting smoother and brighter skin. Gentle exfoliants like AHAs, BHAs, or enzymes work to unclog pores and refine skin texture without causing irritation, which is important for maintaining the smooth, clear base necessary for glass skin.

3. **Toning**: Korean toners are designed to hydrate and balance the skin’s pH, as well as prepare it to absorb serums and moisturizers. Hydrating toners, often infused with ingredients like hyaluronic acid or rose water, deliver essential moisture to the skin, making it appear plump and fresh.

4. **Essences and Serums**: Essences are lightweight, hydrating liquids that help boost the skin’s moisture levels. Serums, on the other hand, are more concentrated and are used to target specific skin concerns such as hyperpigmentation, fine lines, or dullness. Layering these products is key to achieving the deep hydration that gives glass skin its signature reflective quality.

5. **Moisturizing**: A rich, hydrating moisturizer seals in all the previous layers of hydration. Look for moisturizers with humectants like glycerin and hyaluronic acid, which draw moisture into the skin, as well as emollients like ceramides and fatty acids to strengthen the skin barrier and lock in moisture.

6. **Sunscreen**: The final step, and perhaps the most important, is applying sunscreen. UV protection is critical to prevent sun damage, which can lead to premature aging and dull skin. Korean sunscreens are often lightweight and formulated to leave the skin looking dewy, adding to the overall glow.

Why Is Glass Skin So Popular?

The appeal of glass skin lies in its emphasis on natural beauty. Unlike makeup-heavy trends, it focuses on achieving a healthy, radiant complexion that doesn’t rely on cosmetics for coverage. Instead, it encourages a holistic approach to skincare that prioritizes hydration, nourishment, and protection. Moreover, the glow achieved with glass skin makes the face appear youthful, fresh, and vibrant — qualities that are universally desired.

Ultimately, glass skin is more than just a trend; it’s a lifestyle that promotes skincare as a form of self-care, teaching individuals to appreciate the beauty of healthy, well-maintained skin.

text:
FACE SCULPTED & NOSE STRAIGHTENED 
Our lovely patient is back for some maintenance facial sculpting. She is very beautiful, but has some areas she would like us to address- nothing a little bit of filler won't help. Her main concern is balancing her temples; we used a feathering technique to blend her temples while adding some volume as they were becoming hollow, plus we also elevated her brows making her eyes appear more open. We followed the temples with a bit of filler to the jowl area to achieve support, then targeted her nasolabial folds next leaving them softer and less visible. We saved the absolute best for last- her nose. Starting with a small amount of filler to her septum and working our way up the dorsum, we were able to completely transform her nose shape straightening it out. She is over the moon with her results and cannot get over how wonderful she looks!

text:
From greasy to glassy: 5 places you MUST powder 

Translucent tone up powder from @lauramercier 

1. Eyebrows (makes drawing brows easier and helps them last longer)
2. Eyes (similar to brows, makes eye makeup application easier and prevents it from smudging)
3. Smile lines (mattifying smile lines can make you look younger because powder adds subtle volume especially if you use lighter shades)
4. Sides of nose (lots of sebum and pores there -tends to look messy; we only want to focus on highlighting the bridge for dimensional look)
5. Face line (powder outer parts of face to avoid hair from sticking)

text:
~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this tinted hybrid sunscreen from Supergoop today!
🔆
- UV Filters: Zinc Oxide, Homosalate, and Octisalate
- It has a cream texture 
- 14 shades for a wide range of skin tones
- I did not get pilling
- Has a radiant finish
- No added fragrance
- Does not sting my eyes
- Around $44 for 35mL. Can be purchased from their website or Sephora.
🔆
With the amount of coverage and the price, I would say to treat this like a foundation instead of a sunscreen. You can apply the proper amount needed for a sunscreen and it doesn't look bad, but still. Since it has coverage to it, I'm not applying on my neck and beard, etc. I still use my regular sunscreen underneath. Nice product though. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
*Korean Glass Skin: The Ultimate Skincare Trend*

Korean beauty (K-beauty) has taken the global beauty industry by storm, and one of its most iconic trends is the concept of "glass skin." Glass skin refers to a complexion that is incredibly smooth, luminous, and translucent, much like a piece of glass. Achieving this flawless, dewy look is the result of meticulous skincare routines designed to nourish, hydrate, and perfect the skin over time.

At the heart of glass skin is the idea of healthy, well-hydrated skin. It’s not just about masking imperfections or covering up with makeup. Instead, glass skin emphasizes the importance of achieving beauty from within, using a combination of skincare products and techniques that focus on long-term results. The goal is a clear, even-toned complexion that reflects light effortlessly, giving the face a radiant, almost ethereal glow.

The Key Components of a Glass Skin Routine

Achieving glass skin involves a comprehensive skincare regimen, with a focus on hydration, exfoliation, and protection. Here are some key steps:

1. **Double Cleansing**: The first step in the glass skin routine is the K-beauty staple of double cleansing. This process involves using an oil-based cleanser to remove makeup, sunscreen, and impurities, followed by a water-based cleanser to thoroughly clean the skin. Proper cleansing is crucial for preventing breakouts and ensuring that the skin is prepared to absorb subsequent skincare products.

2. **Exfoliation**: Regular exfoliation helps remove dead skin cells, promoting smoother and brighter skin. Gentle exfoliants like AHAs, BHAs, or enzymes work to unclog pores and refine skin texture without causing irritation, which is important for maintaining the smooth, clear base necessary for glass skin.

3. **Toning**: Korean toners are designed to hydrate and balance the skin’s pH, as well as prepare it to absorb serums and moisturizers. Hydrating toners, often infused with ingredients like hyaluronic acid or rose water, deliver essential moisture to the skin, making it appear plump and fresh.

4. **Essences and Serums**: Essences are lightweight, hydrating liquids that help boost the skin’s moisture levels. Serums, on the other hand, are more concentrated and are used to target specific skin concerns such as hyperpigmentation, fine lines, or dullness. Layering these products is key to achieving the deep hydration that gives glass skin its signature reflective quality.

5. **Moisturizing**: A rich, hydrating moisturizer seals in all the previous layers of hydration. Look for moisturizers with humectants like glycerin and hyaluronic acid, which draw moisture into the skin, as well as emollients like ceramides and fatty acids to strengthen the skin barrier and lock in moisture.

6. **Sunscreen**: The final step, and perhaps the most important, is applying sunscreen. UV protection is critical to prevent sun damage, which can lead to premature aging and dull skin. Korean sunscreens are often lightweight and formulated to leave the skin looking dewy, adding to the overall glow.

Why Is Glass Skin So Popular?

The appeal of glass skin lies in its emphasis on natural beauty. Unlike makeup-heavy trends, it focuses on achieving a healthy, radiant complexion that doesn’t rely on cosmetics for coverage. Instead, it encourages a holistic approach to skincare that prioritizes hydration, nourishment, and protection. Moreover, the glow achieved with glass skin makes the face appear youthful, fresh, and vibrant — qualities that are universally desired.

text:
Game On! 🎯 9-Hour Challenge with Estee Lauder Double Wear Stay-in-Place Foundation! ⏳💄

#GiftedByEsteeLauder

People have been raving about the Estee Lauder Double Wear Stay-in-Place Foundation, and I finally got to try it! 😍 It did not disappoint! After testing it for a solid 9 hours, including jogging and having dinner with my besties, my makeup stayed fresh. 💃🏽

My Experience:

There was slight oiliness on my t-zone after jogging but the makeup was still perfectly in place! I simply pressed a tissue on my t-zone to absorb the oil, and — no joke — my makeup didn’t budge! 💪🏽 No cakiness, no oxidation, and I didn’t even use a compact for touch-ups. It lasted flawlessly until late evening! 🌙

Not only did the foundation survive the 9-hour challenge, but it also exceeded my expectations! Truly a fan favorite and the #1 prestige foundation in the US in 2023! 🇺🇸

Product Information:

- Available in over 55 shades 🌈, so you’re bound to find your perfect match!
- 24-hour wear ⏳ for a flawless, natural matte finish 🖌️
- Breathable, lightweight cashmere matte finish 💨
- Coverage: Medium-to-full, buildable 🖤
- Features: Sweat-proof, humidity-proof, waterproof, and transfer-resistant 🏃‍♀️🌧️
- Controls oil all day, no caking or creasing ✨

My Tips: 💧 I wet my makeup sponge, squeeze out the excess water, and gently press the foundation onto my skin for an even, flawless finish. Then, set my makeup with loose powder.

👀 For the delicate under-eye area, I spray a hydrating mist on a brush, pick up a small amount of loose powder, and gently press it in after using Estée Lauder foundation.👌🏽

ACNE SCARS ARE OUT OF HERE

Our patient had suffered severely from her acne scars that she'd carried for years and finally felt ready to do something about them. She saw us on social media and felt confident coming to us because she knew we were the masters of the subcision technique. In addition to subcision, we treated her scars with sculptra to increase collagen production, bellafill to lift the scars and subcise them, Halo, our hybrid fractional laser to attack the scars on multiple levels, and lastly, our profractional laser to penetrate deep and remodel the scars.

She was completely blown away by how effective just one treatment was, but in order for her scars to keep improving, she will require more rounds. text:
I had a delightful time visiting the @louisvuitton x Murakami pop-up in NYC this weekend 🩷💚💜

The pop-up is located on 104 Prince St. in Soho. It features both new pieces from the recent collection as well as archival favorites. In the basement, there is a fun little movie to watch and there is also a room where you can bring your vintage Murakami pieces for repair. Unfortunately, the café has closed after the first two weekends. I waited about 30-40 mins to get inside but there was a virtual queue so I could grab some coffee in soho and relax while I waited.

When I visited this past week, the pop-up did have some of the products in stock, but not many. The only bag that was available was the neverfull. And then they also had some smaller products in stock, such as belts, dog collars, scarves, and sunglasses. For every product that you purchase, you get a token to use on the giant vending machine. You are able to win fun little prizes, like limited edition stickers and Tamagotchi.

If you are a Louis Vuitton Murakami collection lover like me, you will enjoy this little pop-up. However, given that there are very few items to purchase, and the café is closed, there’s not a ton to do for the long wait. I wish that they had more interactive activities or games as well as more archival pieces displayed along the new collection releases.

title: dry skin is no match for this moisturizer 🤯

text:
Products I really want to love but I DON’T 🤯

First thing first, this is my own experience, and skin care results can vary, depending on the skin condition, skin type, environment, and humidity. After all, the products I mentioned below may suit you better. 🙂

1️⃣ Mixsoon Bean Essence - This is a 2-in-1 facial essence that can be used as a moisturizing essence and exfoliating product. 🙁 Unfortunately, I didn’t see any dead skin rub off when I used it as an exfoliator and the hydrating result is just average. There are so many hydrating essences in the market and you can easily find one to replace it.

2️⃣ Anua Peach 77 Niacin Conditioning Milk - I loved it when I first used it but after using this moisturizer for about 2 weeks, I got breakouts here and there. 🙁 I thought it was my hormones but when I stopped using it, my skin was clear. I believe that this moisturizer is actually designed for dry skin and you can even layer it if you want extra moisturizing results, but it doesn’t suit my normal to dry, sometimes oily skin.

3️⃣ Caudalie Vinosource-Hydra Grape Water Gel Moisturizer - the fragrance contained in the product is too strong for my liking, and the product will peel off from the skin when I apply sunscreen or foundation after. 🙁

4️⃣ iT Cosmetics Bye Bye Under Eye Bags Daytime Treatment - this is a daytime under-eye treatment that delivers a temporary depuffing, tightening, and smoothing effect in 15 minutes. My problem is that this eye treatment is too tight and too dry for my skin and ironically, which is also their selling point to tighten and depuff eye bags. 🙁

After using it, I have more fine lines 👵 👀 around eye areas and I have to follow the product instructions every single step - too little is not enough, and too much will be peeling off! Need to use my fingertips to tab when applying, can’t smile or squint till it is dry, and use it after makeup. There are so many rules to follow. 🤯

😅 It may be my issue as the reviews of this product are good but it just doesn’t suit me.

Have you tried these products? Let me know your experience and share with us what products disappoint you 🙁.

text:
~
I got many people asking me to do a try on or share my thoughts when I posted about getting this recently on my story. But the photo I posted last week is an old photo from when I got this back in December, so I've actually been using this for a while lol. Needless to say, I can say I love it (and the other Danessa Myricks Beauty products I've tried).
✨
Just showing here how I usually use it. I start off with priming using the Yummy Skin Blurring Balm Powder in Universal to help control my oils throughout the day, and then go into the Skin Tint. This tint is really nice on the skin. Looks very smooth with a nice natural glow. Can be a solid light/medium coverage option. There is more coverage when I use it with a brush, but I used a sponge this day. I follow up with a deeper shade of the Blurring Balm Powder for sort of bronze the perimeter of my face. After locking it in with a setting spray and powder, it's good to go.
✨
Let me know if you have any specific questions about my experience using it, but I'm loving it. It is very quick and easy to apply. It lasts well on me throughout the day, especially with the Blurring Balm Powder as a primer and proper setting after. Just helps to naturally elevate by evening out the appearance of my skin without being too full coverage.

text:
🌿✨ New Product Alert! Medicube Exosome Cica Calming Collection ✨🌿

🌟 The Medicube Exosome Cica Calming line is crafted for all skin types, especially those prone to irritation and breakouts. 

Thanks to Medicube for sending me this skincare series for an honest review! 🙌 I’ve been testing these lightweight products in high-humidity weather, and they’ve been perfect for my combo skin. Among them, the Exosome Cica Calming Ampoule stands out as my favorite. 💧 Its watery-gel texture rehydrates my skin beautifully, and I use it day and night after an AHA/BHA toner and before my acne treatment for a soothing effect. 🌱💖

🌱 What is Exosome Cica Calming Ampoule? This powerhouse ampoule uses Exosome Cica, a nano-sized ingredient with 5.3x the soothing power of traditional cica! It calms skin troubles, smooths texture, and provides long-lasting hydration with a refreshing, non-greasy feel. Perfect for AM or PM use! 🌅🌙

🌿 What are Exosome Cica Calming Toner Pads? Each pad provides a gentle swipe of hydration, balance, and skin-softening. Made with Tea Tree Leaf Water and Exosome Cica, these pads help with pore care and sebum control. 🧖‍♀️✨ 

My Experience: Convenient to use and leaves my skin feeling smooth! I’m still seeing if it will help with my large pores, but it’s a great addition to my routine.

💧 Exosome Cica Calming Cream: This cream offers up to 48 hours of hydration with a lightweight, non-sticky feel which is perfect for under makeup for a fresh, dewy look! 💦 It’s colorless, fragrance-free, and suitable for everyday use, especially for troubled or sensitive skin. 

My Experience: A gentle, calming moisturizer for all skin types! I love using it alongside my acne treatment for added hydration without any greasy residue. It’s a fantastic basic moisturizer for daily use! ✨

Key Ingredients:
🍀 Exosome Cica: 5.3x more soothing than regular cica
🍃 Tea Tree Leaf Water: Calms and hydrates troubled skin
🥰 Niacinamide: Brightens, strengthens, and reduces irritation

text:
12 Ways to Improve Understanding Facial Asymmetry: Causes, Effects, and Solutions

 1.Consult a Professional
Seek advice from a dermatologist, orthodontist, or plastic surgeon to get a proper diagnosis and treatment plan for facial asymmetry.
#ProfessionalConsultation #ExpertAdvice

 2.Understand Genetic Factors
Learn about how genetics play a role in facial asymmetry. It’s often hereditary, so understanding your family history can provide insights.
#Genetics #FamilyHistory

 3.Consider Orthodontic Treatment
Braces, retainers, or other orthodontic treatments can correct jaw alignment and improve facial symmetry over time.
#Orthodontics #JawAlignment

 4.Practice Facial Exercises
Certain facial exercises can strengthen and balance the muscles on both sides of your face, reducing asymmetry.
#FacialExercises #MuscleBalance

 5.Improve Your Posture
Poor posture can contribute to facial asymmetry. Work on standing and sitting straight to maintain an even facial structure.
#Posture #BodyAlignment

 6.Monitor Your Sleeping Position
Sleeping on one side can cause facial asymmetry. Try to alternate sides or sleep on your back to minimize this effect.
#SleepingPosition #SymmetryTips

7.Massage Therapy
Regular facial massages can improve blood circulation and help relax overactive muscles, contributing to a more symmetrical appearance.
#FacialMassage #BloodCirculation

8. **Consider Dermal Fillers
Non-surgical options like dermal fillers can be used to correct minor asymmetries by adding volume to specific areas of the face.
#DermalFillers #NonSurgicalTreatment

9.Surgical Options
For more severe cases, surgical procedures like rhinoplasty, jaw surgery, or chin implants may be considered to correct facial asymmetry.
#FacialSurgery #CorrectiveProcedures

10.Cosmetic Camouflage Techniques
Learn makeup techniques that help balance your facial features, enhancing symmetry with contouring and highlighting.
#MakeupTips #CosmeticCamouflage

11.Manage Environmental Factors
Sun exposure, facial injuries, and even habitual expressions can contribute to asymmetry. Protect your skin and be mindful of these factors.
#EnvironmentalFactors #SkinProtection

12.Accept and Embrace Your Unique Features
While improvement is possible, remember that a certain degree of asymmetry is natural and contributes to your unique beauty. Embrace it!
#SelfAcceptance #UniqueBeauty

These 12 points offer a comprehensive approach to understanding and addressing facial asymmetry, combining both practical tips and professional solutions.

text:
How to Draw a Natural Eyeliner?

1️⃣ Use a powder puff to gently press the outer corner of your eye, then slightly lift it.
2️⃣ Start drawing from the middle (or even the outer third) of your upper eyelid.
3️⃣ Extend the line from the inner corner of your eye.
4️⃣ Connect the dots and fill in any gaps.
5️⃣ Finally, extend the tail of your eyeliner for a flawless finish.

🖤 Product I Used: Wet n Wild Breakup Proof Waterproof Liquid Eyeliner — perfect for a sharp and smooth look!

Tip: Avoid blinking until the eyeliner is fully dry! 😉

If you haven't tried this formula, it's a thick, cushiony lip balm with great grip that coats the lips with nourishment. It has a pretty noticeable grape scent and the level of pigment depends on the shade you're getting. There isn't any smoothing quality but they're a nice shiny lip balm.

The only con to the Jello Gloss Balms is the shade range. There are 5 variations of pink, 1 clear, 1 clear with shimmer, 2 nudes, 1 plum, and 1 orange. We need berries, browns, reds, and beiges!

text:
Lavender Gel Nail Designs Short Tutorial - Inspired by Japanese Gel Nail Art 🌸💜

Remember I posted a reel about the lavender jade gel nail design? Well, I finally found some time to finish shooting it, and it was so much fun! It may not be perfect, but the process was quite soothing and felt like a form of meditation as it completely occupied my mind. 🧘‍♀️✨

For this design, I only used a few gel nail polishes and purple glitters that I bought from Japan. You can easily find these products on several shopping platforms in the US. 

✅ Tips: Gel nail polishes in jello finish are recommended for this gemstone design. If you can’t find jello gel nail polish, mix regular gel nail colors with base gel and apply it to the nails with a brush. This will also create a semi-transparent effect. 💅🌟

😍 Steps by Steps of My Design:

1) Apply base gel, then 2-3 layers of jello gel polish (purple in this design) 💜

2) Apply glitters diagonally and cure them ✨

3) Apply top coat and cure it 💅

4) File the uneven surface and brush the surface to remove the dust 🖌️

5) Use a nail brush to apply a white line and blur it in one direction 🎨

6) Cure it and apply a top coat ✨

7) Re-apply the jello gel polish on partial areas to create an in-depth 3D effect 💎 

8) Finish it with top coat and cure it 

Will you try DIY gel nails at home? 💜💅

text:
~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this body sunscreen from Naked Sundays today! 
🔆
- UV Filters: Homosalate, Octocrylene, Avobenzone, and Octisalate
- It has a light lotion texture
- No white cast on my skin tone
- Works well in my body hair
- Has a natural glowy finish (dry touch feel, but shimmers)
- No added fragrance or essential oils
- Around $34 for 100mL. Can be purchased from their website.
🔆
I assume that this would look good on a variety of skin tones and almost would give like a self tanner type of look if you have a lighter skin tone. It gives a glow to the skin without being greasy because it does sink in very well to the skin. You just get that glow and radiance from the golden shimmer. I almost wish that it did have a little bit of a sweet tropical scent like the other body sunscreen because this does seem like a special occasion, vacation type of vibe. I wouldn’t go sit on a white chair while wearing the sunscreen and honestly just because of that I probably would not repurchase this. I don’t have to be cautious of where I’m touching because of a tinted body product but I know that’s not the case for everyone. I know some people are totally cool with that. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
Fitglow launched two new shades of their cloud collagen lipstick balm in rosewood and peony, and a new shade of their vegan lip liner in muted mauve.

The cloud collagen balms are like a semi-matte lipstick meets a silky lip balm. They have some slip/creaminess to them that I really enjoy alongside really good grip. I would prefer if they came in a traditional lipstick bullet because they’re so pigmented but that’s a minor flaw.

The vegan lip liners are lovely, they are pretty sturdy so they stay in place really well but still have a creaminess to them, which I love. I don’t like lip liners that fully dry down so these are one of my favorite formulas.

Gladiator liposuction is seldom about weight loss. It's all about sculpting and giving my patients the confidence to take on the world with a physique that reflects your hard work. I use the most advanced technology available such as Vaser and Renuvion with expert precision to deliver the most defined, athletic results possible.

Each treatment plan is meticulously customized to your unique anatomy and aesthetic goals. Whether you’re looking to enhance muscle definition or achieve a leaner, more chiseled look, I use the latest techniques like high-definition liposuction to carve out your abs, chest, arms, and back, creating a body that’s as strong as it looks.

For optimal results, I incorporate specialized fat-removal strategies that highlight muscle contours and deliver precise, natural-looking results. This not only refines the surface but also creates a more athletic, masculine appearance—perfectly suited for those aiming for that gladiator look.

What sets my practice apart is my deep understanding of different body types and how to approach each one for the best results. With over 15 years of experience in body contouring, I’ve perfected the art of achieving a balanced, proportional outcome that accentuates muscle definition without sacrificing a natural look.

I’ve performed thousands of procedures, sculpting stronger, more defined physiques for patients ready to live their most confident lives. Every body is unique, which is why I tailor each gladiator liposuction procedure to bring out the strongest, most refined version of you.

text:
3 things that have changed the health of my skin:
1. I double cleanse every night but I skip a morning cleanse, now everyone is different so this may not work for some but I find that it helps my skin feel and look less dry while preserving my barrier. 
2. Exfoliating. This is a big one. I feel like the internet always tells us to exfoliate regularly but my skin doesn’t usually like it more than once in a while if I feel I need it. I always say go off of what your skin needs versus what the internet tells you. For me retinol helps me achieve smooth skin anyway so I don’t feel like I need it much. 

3. I use retinol every night, usually a retinal or even a gentle retinol. I prefer retinals since they have an encapsulated delivery method which keeps them stable and minimizes irritation. Since I have sensitive skin I usually use a sandwich method with moisturizer and really make sure I stick to a pea sized amount. I prefer using retinols over exfoliants because they achieve all of the same results and now that my skin is used to them, my barrier prefers it.

text:
Glossier launched their Lip Line Lip Liners and I bought the shade Grip.

Grip is described as cool rose but on me it’s pretty warm. I wouldn’t wear it as a liner because the color is so bright and I prefer more muted / natural contour shades, but this is a gorgeous all-over-the-lips color. 

This formula is super creamy but sets in about 2 seconds and once it’s dry it does not budge. It’s not the kind of formula you can smudge - it will legitimately crumble off if you try to smudge it because it sets so fast. 

Because it has a budge-proof finish, it can feel a bit drying, so I like to add a gloss or balm on top.

These are $18 and the colors are “nipple matched,” which is apparently supposed to help you find your best color. 

You’re learning a lot about me here. but my nips are light pink and I definitely don’t want that as a lip liner color lol. Idk about that logic but maybe it works better for other skin tones.

Overall, at $18 this is a great long-lasting formula, I just wish they had some shades that were actually cool toned.

Lip Line at Sephora: https://rstyle.me/+dEZlVR3l8w5va4-YFnnPBQ

Pinky Glowy Skin: Medicube PDRN Pink Peptide Serum 🌸 

This serum is a powerhouse for anyone looking to boost skin elasticity and reduce dark spots while promoting a radiant glow. ✨ It’s been formulated with some seriously impressive ingredients:

- Rose PDRN (Polydeoxyribonucleotide): A vegan-friendly option that combines Rosa Damascena Extract with Sodium DNA to restore your skin’s natural barrier and boost elasticity. 🌹💪

- 5 Types of Peptide Complex: Firm up your skin and reduce fine lines by boosting collagen production. 💖✨

- Niacinamide: Brightens your complexion, strengthens the skin barrier, and calms irritation. 🌟

- Adenosine: Smooths out fine lines and supports healthy skin structure. 🙌

- Holy Basil Extract: Soothes and protects your skin from irritation. 🍃

I’ve been pairing this serum with my Medicube Age-R Booster Pro to maximize the benefits. The milky, lotion-like texture is perfect for cooler, dry weather, and it helps the device glide smoothly over my skin. After just 10 minutes of treatment (5 minutes in Booster mode and 5 minutes in MC mode at Level 1), my skin feels soft, nourished, and glossy. 💦

Although it’s too early to see dramatic brightening results, I’m confident that with consistent use, my skin will look more radiant, thanks to the impressive before-and-after pictures on their website. 🌟

If you’re looking for a serum that combines cutting-edge ingredients with luxurious texture, this one’s a must-try!

text:
*Korean Glass Skin: The Ultimate Skincare Trend*

Korean beauty (K-beauty) has taken the global beauty industry by storm, and one of its most iconic trends is the concept of "glass skin." Glass skin refers to a complexion that is incredibly smooth, luminous, and translucent, much like a piece of glass. Achieving this flawless, dewy look is the result of meticulous skincare routines designed to nourish, hydrate, and perfect the skin over time.

At the heart of glass skin is the idea of healthy, well-hydrated skin. It’s not just about masking imperfections or covering up with makeup. Instead, glass skin emphasizes the importance of achieving beauty from within, using a combination of skincare products and techniques that focus on long-term results. The goal is a clear, even-toned complexion that reflects light effortlessly, giving the face a radiant, almost ethereal glow.

The Key Components of a Glass Skin Routine

Achieving glass skin involves a comprehensive skincare regimen, with a focus on hydration, exfoliation, and protection. Here are some key steps:

1. **Double Cleansing**: The first step in the glass skin routine is the K-beauty staple of double cleansing. This process involves using an oil-based cleanser to remove makeup, sunscreen, and impurities, followed by a water-based cleanser to thoroughly clean the skin. Proper cleansing is crucial for preventing breakouts and ensuring that the skin is prepared to absorb subsequent skincare products.

2. **Exfoliation**: Regular exfoliation helps remove dead skin cells, promoting smoother and brighter skin. Gentle exfoliants like AHAs, BHAs, or enzymes work to unclog pores and refine skin texture without causing irritation, which is important for maintaining the smooth, clear base necessary for glass skin.

3. **Toning**: Korean toners are designed to hydrate and balance the skin’s pH, as well as prepare it to absorb serums and moisturizers. Hydrating toners, often infused with ingredients like hyaluronic acid or rose water, deliver essential moisture to the skin, making it appear plump and fresh.

4. **Essences and Serums**: Essences are lightweight, hydrating liquids that help boost the skin’s moisture levels. Serums, on the other hand, are more concentrated and are used to target specific skin concerns such as hyperpigmentation, fine lines, or dullness. Layering these products is key to achieving the deep hydration that gives glass skin its signature reflective quality.

5. **Moisturizing**: A rich, hydrating moisturizer seals in all the previous layers of hydration. Look for moisturizers with humectants like glycerin and hyaluronic acid, which draw moisture into the skin, as well as emollients like ceramides and fatty acids to strengthen the skin barrier and lock in moisture.

6. **Sunscreen**: The final step, and perhaps the most important, is applying sunscreen. UV protection is critical to prevent sun damage, which can lead to premature aging and dull skin. Korean sunscreens are often lightweight and formulated to leave the skin looking dewy, adding to the overall glow.

Why Is Glass Skin So Popular?

The appeal of glass skin lies in its emphasis on natural beauty. Unlike makeup-heavy trends, it focuses on achieving a healthy, radiant complexion that doesn’t rely on cosmetics for coverage. Instead, it encourages a holistic approach to skincare that prioritizes hydration, nourishment, and protection. Moreover, the glow achieved with glass skin makes the face appear youthful, fresh, and vibrant — qualities that are universally desired.

✨ Want to firm your skin at home without spending a fortune at the salon?

💫 YesStyle Code: BEAUTYKAT321 
💫 Olive Young Global Code: BEAUTYKAT321
💫 Save10%-15% Off at Stylevana! Stylevana Code: INF10KATUSA 

The Medicube Age-R Booster Pro ($288) is your new skincare BFF! 🌟 It goes viral for a reason - it has 4 modes for different skin care needs and today, I am going to use Booster Mode for boosting product absorption, and Micro Current (MC) Mode for skin firming.

I love pairing it with a Collagen Jelly Cream for that smooth glide, but feel free to use your favorite hydrating serum or a sheet mask! 🧖‍♀️

Unlike other skin care devices, they require using products without oil. For Medicube, you can use almost everything with it except aggressive skincare ingredients, such as AHA and Retinol, etc.

💫 For the Booster Mode, I started from level 1 and used it in a circular motion for 5 mins. Then, I switched to MC Mode and pulled my skin upward from the inside out for another 5 mins. I only used the device on one side of my face so you can see the before and after results.

After using it, my jawline and eyebrow are slightly lifted. 🥰 To prolong the skincare benefits, it is recommended to use the device 1-3 times a day but I won’t follow the recommendation as the device is too strong for frequent use, and it’s too time consuming. ⏳

Using this device with a cool sheet mask is more effective - my skin is softer and brighter, and the firming result is more obvious.

Thanks to @medicube_global_official and @medicube_us for sending me Medicube Age-R Booster Pro, I can see that I won’t visit beauty salons like I used to! By the way, should I make another reel for using Booster Pro with a facial sheet mask? Tell me what you think. 👇

text:
Korean Glass Skin: The Ultimate Skincare Trend 

Korean beauty (K-beauty) has taken the global beauty industry by storm, and one of its most iconic trends is the concept of "glass skin." Glass skin refers to a complexion that is incredibly smooth, luminous, and translucent, much like a piece of glass. Achieving this flawless, dewy look is the result of meticulous skincare routines designed to nourish, hydrate, and perfect the skin over time.

At the heart of glass skin is the idea of healthy, well-hydrated skin. It’s not just about masking imperfections or covering up with makeup. Instead, glass skin emphasizes the importance of achieving beauty from within, using a combination of skincare products and techniques that focus on long-term results. The goal is a clear, even-toned complexion that reflects light effortlessly, giving the face a radiant, almost ethereal glow.

   The Key Components of a Glass Skin Routine

Achieving glass skin involves a comprehensive skincare regimen, with a focus on hydration, exfoliation, and protection. Here are some key steps:

1.  Double Cleansing : The first step in the glass skin routine is the K-beauty staple of double cleansing. This process involves using an oil-based cleanser to remove makeup, sunscreen, and impurities, followed by a water-based cleanser to thoroughly clean the skin. Proper cleansing is crucial for preventing breakouts and ensuring that the skin is prepared to absorb subsequent skincare products.

2.  Exfoliation : Regular exfoliation helps remove dead skin cells, promoting smoother and brighter skin. Gentle exfoliants like AHAs, BHAs, or enzymes work to unclog pores and refine skin texture without causing irritation, which is important for maintaining the smooth, clear base necessary for glass skin.

3.  Toning : Korean toners are designed to hydrate and balance the skin’s pH, as well as prepare it to absorb serums and moisturizers. Hydrating toners, often infused with ingredients like hyaluronic acid or rose water, deliver essential moisture to the skin, making it appear plump and fresh.

4.   Essences and Serums: Essences are lightweight, hydrating liquids that help boost the skin’s moisture levels. Serums, on the other hand, are more concentrated and are used to target specific skin concerns such as hyperpigmentation, fine lines, or dullness. Layering these products is key to achieving the deep hydration that gives glass skin its signature reflective quality.

5.  Moisturizing : A rich, hydrating moisturizer seals in all the previous layers of hydration. Look for moisturizers with humectants like glycerin and hyaluronic acid, which draw moisture into the skin, as well as emollients like ceramides and fatty acids to strengthen the skin barrier and lock in moisture.

6. Sunscreen : The final step, and perhaps the most important, is applying sunscreen. UV protection is critical to prevent sun damage, which can lead to premature aging and dull skin. Korean sunscreens are often lightweight and formulated to leave the skin looking dewy, adding to the overall glow.

   Why Is Glass Skin So Popular?

The appeal of glass skin lies in its emphasis on natural beauty. Unlike makeup-heavy trends, it focuses on achieving a healthy, radiant complexion that doesn’t rely on cosmetics for coverage. Instead, it encourages a holistic approach to skincare that prioritizes hydration, nourishment, and protection. Moreover, the glow achieved with glass skin makes the face appear youthful, fresh, and vibrant — qualities that are universally desired.

✨ Brightening Power: Packed with 20,000ppm of niacinamide and Vitamin C to tackle hyperpigmentation and give me a radiant glow.

text:
Adorable Lip Tint from Japan 🇯🇵 - CANMAKE Muchi Puru Tint 💄✨

I recently bought some makeup products from Japan, and CANMAKE is one of them. This brand won me over as it offers a spectrum of high-quality makeup products at affordable prices with kawaii packaging. 🌸✨

I bought CANMAKE Muchi Puru Tint in:

01 Butterscotch 🍬

02 Peach 🍑

03 Wine Berry 🍇

05 Fig Puree 🎈

Thanks to the hydrating and moisturizing agents - Petroleum, Hyaluronic Acid, Collagen, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil, Honey, and Shea Butter - this lip tint provides a hint of cooling sensation, it also moisturizes my lips for long hours without feeling sticky.

The texture is soft, easy to glide on the lips, and won’t bleed. The color stays on the lips and conceals vertical lip lines, and most importantly, they are free from Fragrance, Parabens, Alcohol, and Silicone. How cool is that? 🤩

🤔 Although the product is called a lip tint, the color is not long-lasting, and you have to re-apply it after drinking and eating. It doesn’t bother me much, but it might for some people.

Will I repurchase it? I definitely will. 💖

text:
ALL SKIN TYPES ARE WELCOME

The most common case that we use lasers in is for acne scars, but we also often use lasers for anti-aging purposes in order to revitalize the skin. There is undoubtedly a risk when it comes to treating patients with darker skin tones, but here at our practice, that risk is heavily mitigated due to our years of experience in treating all kinds of skin types. From skin type 1 to skin type 6, we don't shy away from treating any patient. This is because we are well-versed in the many different ways to treat different skin types. Make no mistake, laser treatments are not one size fits all. Some lasers that are excellent for fairer skin types are incredibly dangerous for darker ones. The improper use of a laser on a darker skin type can result in a burn or other unwanted pigmentation. It is an absolute MUST that you go to someone experienced who knows exactly how to treat darker skin types if you have dark skin.
We specialize in the use of many lasers such as Halo, CO2, Profractional, Aerolase, Fraxel, and more! We are at the top of our field in safely treating acne scars or even just rejuvenating the skin with lasers.

Acne scars are more than just a skin issue—they absolutely crush the confidence of my patients. This patient came to me feeling frustrated and self-conscious about his stubborn acne scars. They not only affected his appearance, but they also stopped him from feeling his best. 

My approach was to use a combination treatment to address both the texture and pigmentation. I used TCA Cross, Halo laser, and CO2 laser to resurface and regenerate the skin. Each of these treatments is a powerhouse on its own, but combined, they worked MAGIC to improve the look and feel of his skin.
We also incorporated the Glacial Glide in combination with AnteAGE Exosomes and EMER Skin for advanced healing and skin regeneration, ensuring that the results would not only be effective but long-lasting.

 His scars are noticeably smoother, the discoloration has dramatically faded, and his skin is looking healthier than ever. RETURNING FOR MORE CONTOUR

Our patient recently came to us for a surgical procedure where we removed his buccal fat pads in order to get him a slimmer look in his cheeks. We also performed some neck lipo on him in order to achieve a snatched jawline. Now that he has healed, he's back to build upon those results with some radiesse filler to his midface, jawline, and chin. The previous procedure is going to enable his filler to really pop so he was excited to see his results. Once everything settled, he was extremely satisfied with the sharper, more angular look we gave him. It was exactly what he envisioned when he came to us and he could not be happier.

text:
💕 Perfect duo for dehydrated skin 💦 Haruharu Wonder Black Rice Hyaluronic Toner and Black Rice Facial Oil 💕

YesStyle.com Reward Code 👉 BEAUTYKAT321 👈 

I am using 🥰 Haruharu Wonder Black Rice Hyaluronic Toner 🥰 which is a light, hydrating, and refreshing toner packed with fermented ingredients, such as 🌾 Rice Extracts, 🎋 Panax Ginseng Root Extract and 💦 Hyaluronic Acid. I love how it softens and smooths my skin right after a single application. It also helps skin absorption for subsequent use of essence, serum, and moisturizer.

I brought the Haruharu Wonder Black Rice Hyaluronic Toner for my recent Thailand trip. My friend and my husband loved it! They both have dry skin so I encourage them to use it generously after sunbathing. They splashed the toner onto their palm and patted it on the skin. It is great for rehydrating thirsty and sun-damaged skin and you can see the result instantly.

After the toner, I use Vitamin C serum and then layer with 🥰 Haruharu Wonder Black Rice Facial Oil 🥰 which is a lightweight facial oil for amazing fast-absorbing, and skin moisturizing results. I have normal to dry skin so sometimes, I need facial oil to replenish my skin’s natural moisture. I like Haruharu Wonder Black Rice Facial Oil as it is easy to spread out and absorb. It creates a dewy, glassy skin finish without feeling heavy which is simply amazing. 

I also use this facial oil on the neck and body, and if the weather is too dry, I will mix it with my regular moisturizer or body lotion for extra nourishment. The best part is that I can use it after snail mucin essence or other serums to boost the skincare benefits and repair the skin barrier. It contains 🌾 45% Rice Bran Oil, 🌻 Sunflower Seed Oil, 🪻 Lavender Oil, and 🍃 Jojoba Oil so you can also use it as a massage oil for relaxing.

The only complaint I have is the scent of this facial oil. It is Lavender but I think it is a bit too strong for my liking. Having said that, it doesn’t irritate my skin at all and I can even apply it to my under-eye areas (use it cautiously if you have sensitive eyes).

Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this body sunscreen from Coola today! 
🔆
- UV Filters: Avobenzone, Homosalate, Octisalate, and Octocrylene
- It has a lotion texture
- No white cast on my skin tone
- Works well in my body hair
- Has a natural glowy finish with a dry touch feel
- No added fragrance but they have scented versions
- Water and sweat resistant
- Around $28 for 148mL. Can be purchased from their website, sephora, or ulta.
🔆
I loved their spray version of this and this is just as good. Water resistance is super important for a body sunscreen for me and it didn't start breaking down easily with sweat. This could be a good option to make sure you're getting good even coverage compared to the spray. This also comes in SPF 30, 50, 70, and scent options. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

Our patient came to us wanting to see a higher level of sculpting in his body, particularly his arms. He had a vision of those hulking, super defined arms and he just wasn't able to achieve them with just his dedicated work in the gym. So, we went to work and carefully sculpted them out while grafting fat to his shoulders in order to round them. Many doctors are unwilling to perform liposuction in this area, as the anatomy is very delicate and requires only the utmost knowledge and skill. He chose us based on the high amount of results we post on our socials, so he felt extremely comfortable trusting us. We know the exact area to sculpt and were able to really define each critical area of his arms: his biceps, triceps, deltoid, and the shoulders. This latter portion was done by harvesting his fat, purifying it, and then grafting it into the shoulders in order to athletically round them, creating immaculate balance with his arms. ​We did more than just his shoulders and arms.
     IT DOESN'T END WITH SURGERY
He got stellar results from his procedure, but he wanted to get the absolute most out of it. He also made sure he was eating right, working hard in the gym, and taking PEPTIDES such as MK-677 and CJC for muscle growth and growth hormone production. This stands as an excellent example of a patient who put in the work post-surgery to truly capitalize on and maximize his results.

text:
Yep, delayed retinoid irritation is a thing!

Most folks think that if they don't feel irritation within 24hrs of applying a retinoid, they are in the safe zone. But did you know retinoids can cause a delayed irritation response that is felt up to 3 days later?😳

👉This tip mostly applies to folks new to the retinoid game or those increasing the strength of their current retinoid.

So remember, if you're new to the game or upleveling, tune into your skin past the first 24hrs and let your skintuition guide your retinoid journey!

Thanks to @medicube_global_official for sending me several products for review, including these best-selling moisturizers I’ve long wanted to try!

Now, the questions are, which one should we use, and what’s the best price we can get online? I’ve laid out the differences between these moisturizers below, and you can enjoy the discounted prices on Prime Day. 🎉

🌸 What is Medicube Collagen Niacinamide Jelly Cream? It’s a hydrating and anti-aging cream designed to improve skin elasticity and moisture levels.

🌸 Key Ingredients
* Collagen
* Niacinamide
* Hyaluronic Acid
* Peptides

🌸 Skincare Functions
* Boosts skin elasticity
* Provides deep hydration
* Reduces fine lines and wrinkles
* Improves saggy skin

💛 What is Medicube Deep Vita C Capsule Cream? It’s an innovative skincare product that combines a transparent gel with Vitamin C capsules to deliver a fresh, potent dose of Vitamin C with each use.

💛 Key Ingredients
* Vitamin C
* Hyaluronic Acid
* Ceramides
* Niacinamide

💛 Skincare Functions
* Brightens complexion
* Evens skin tone
* Reduces hyperpigmentation
* Provides antioxidant protection

🌸 🤔  What do I think about Medicube Collagen Niacinamide Jelly Cream? It’s more suitable for dry skin with aging concerns. I love using it as a sleeping pack to seal in my natural skin’s moisture, especially when the air-con is on overnight. I wake up with soft, glowy & hydrated skin. I use it 2-3 times a week or as needed.

💛 🤔 What do I think about Medicube Deep Vita C Capsule Cream? This cream feels like an advanced skincare product straight from the future! I love playing around with the transparent gel and Vitamin C capsules.

💡 For oily and combination skin: 1 part of transparent gel to 1 part of Vita C capsule.💡 For dry skin: 1 part of gel and 2 parts of Vita C capsule.

It provides a subtle, instant glow to my skin without feeling heavy. I use it twice a day with my face serum, regular sunscreen, and makeup, and the finish is perfect! It‘s suitable for all skin types and ideal for those looking to improve complexion and even out skin tone.

text:
Ellis Brooklyn sent me their new perfume in Miami Nectar and it’s lovely!

Notes:
Pink Pineapple, Palm Leaves, Coconut Water
Wild Jasmine, Plumeria, Lily of the Valley
Tree Moss, Salted Woods, Sweet Amber Woods, Vanilla

At first, I get a burst of pineapple but that quickly fades into three distinct notes: coconut, florals, and a salty, woody accord.

Miami Nectar is described as a gourmand but I smell the florals just as much as I smell coconut and salted and amber woods, so it’s quite balanced! If you’re not a gourmand lover, don’t let that scare you off.

Longevity is on the lighter side but I don’t mind reapplying.

Overall, I’d say Miami Nectar is my second favorite perfume from Ellis Brooklyn. Nothing could ever beat my love of Sun Fruit, it’s my signature warm weather scent!

Miami Nectar at Sephora: https://rstyle.me/+TvwRpzIKNJk9x9cp8VUIqA
