Acne scars are a source of embarrassment and dejection for millions of people, and I see it in my practice all the time. My patient came to me with deep frustration over her scars, and like many others, it was affecting her confidence in a big way. This is her second treatment with me, and I’m thrilled to see how far she’s come.

For her, I used a combination of TCA Cross, Halo laser, and CO2 resurfacing—treatments that I’ve perfected over the years to address every layer of scarring. It’s not just about picking the right treatments—it’s about knowing exactly how to use them to get safe, effective results. I see a lot of people who go to less experienced providers and don’t get the results they’re hoping for. When it comes to acne scars, you need someone who understands the nuances of different skin types and how to treat them safely and effectively. That’s what I bring to the table with every patient.

This case is a perfect example of why expertise matters. The wrong treatment or technique can lead to complications like hyperpigmentation or underwhelming results, but with my experience, I’ve been able to safely deliver remarkable improvement. But no treatment is complete without proper aftercare. I always recommend my patients use my EMER SKIN products post-procedure to maximize their results. It’s a crucial step in reducing downtime, supporting the healing process, and ensuring that their skin continues to improve long after the treatment is done.

If you’re dealing with acne scars, don’t settle for less than an expert. I’ve spent years honing my techniques to give my patients the best possible outcome. Your skin deserves nothing less.

text:
Will you choose a toner pad with a higher price or a cheaper one? 🤔

Let’s compare K-Beauty brands, the Medicube Zero Pore Pad 2.0 and the Farmstay Tea Tree Biome Calming Toner Pad. Both contain acids, AHA and PHA respectively, that improve skin texture, target large pores, and exfoliate the skin. 🌟

1️⃣ Medicube Zero Pore Pad

Removes excess oil and impurities while exfoliating the skin to improve large pores.
Dual-textured pads infused with Salicylic Acid (BHA) and AHA, plus patented pore care ingredients to exfoliate dead skin cells, clear sebum, and minimize pores.

2️⃣ Farmstay Tea Tree Biome Calming Toner Pad

Contains PHA, which has a larger molecular structure than AHA, making it gentler on the skin.

Infused with Tea Tree Leaf Oil and Extract to hydrate and calm the skin while maintaining oil-water balance.

😌 What do I think about these toner pads?

Medicube:
✅ Better oil control.
✅ Contains more essence, so one pad is enough for the face, neck, and collar areas.
🚫 Not suitable as a mini face mask as it can dry out the skin.
🚫 Higher price: $17 on Amazon, $20.8 on Stylevana, and $27 on YesStyle.

Farmstay:
✅ Gentler on the skin with soothing ingredients.
✅ Offers light hydration.
✅ Can be used as a toner pad or mini face mask.
✅ More competitive price: $10.39 at Stylevana.
🚫 Less effective in controlling oil and refining pores.

After all, I prefer the 💙 Medicube Zero Pore Pad 2.0 for summer when the high humidity and hot weather make my skin feel heavy and oily. It’s a bit pricey but I think it’s worth every penny.

However, Farmstay may suit you better if you have a combination to dry skin and are on a budget.

⚠️ Remarks: Don’t mix AHA, BHA, and PHA with Vitamin C and Retinol. If you use Niacinamide, apply it at different times of the day or at least 30 minutes apart.

text:
YSL sent me three shades of their new Make Me Blush 12H Blurring Liquid Blushes!

They’re $39 each and come in 6 shades.

Description says they’re “A highly pigmented and creamy liquid-to-powder blush that's blendable, buildable, and melts into skin for a blurring, soft-cloud finish and up to 12 hours of wear.”

I fully agree with the description (how refreshing!) They remind me of the Rare Beauty liquid blushes but I find these to be slightly less pigmented, which gives me more control. But a little still goes a very long way, as I learned when I applied these for the first time in this reel. You really only need one dot.

My skin EATS blush so I rarely have high hopes for blush that claims to be long-lasting, but these blew me away. I love the soft matte finish, which helps the product last longer on my skin, and I really hope YSL expands this shade range! This one’s a banger. 

The price tag is steep but it’s worth it for me to splurge on a product that’s easy to apply and doesn’t fade quickly. I’m definitely going to buy the shade 44 Nude Lavalliere!

text:
Ilia sent me their new Skin Rewind Blurring Foundation and Concealer Complexion Stick in 5C Pine and I have mixed thoughts!

On one hand, Ilia has made HUGE improvements with their shade range. This has a whopping 42 shades!

I love that this has buildable medium coverage, but it’s quite stiff to blend and the soft matte finish gets VERY oily on my combination skin. I just feel like it don’t make me look very good, but I’m very grateful to Ilia for sending me the product in PR.

I’ve heard from a lot of people that this gets oily, so I wouldn’t purchase it if you’re looking for a true soft matte finish.

What do you think? Have you tried this?

💖 Soft Glow Goals with Lilybyred Luv Beam Cheek Balm! 💖

*Gifted by YesStyle 

Say hello to a subtle glow and natural flush with lilybyred Luv Beam Cheek Balm in #2 Innocent Pink! 🌸 This creamy, buildable blush has stolen my heart (literally, just look at the cute heart-shaped packaging! 💕). Here’s why I love it:

✨ Glow Up: Adds soft, glowy color to cheeks for that perfect flushed look.

🎨 Buildable Formula: Go sheer for a natural vibe or layer up for a bold pop of color—no caking, no stickiness!

🌿 Skin Brightening: The lavender undertone of #2 Innocent Pink blends beautifully with my warm skin tone, brightening dull complexions effortlessly.

👩‍🎨 Easy to Use: Apply with your fingertip or a makeup puff for a seamless blend.

While I wouldn’t use it on my lips (the shade’s a bit light for me), it’s a total win for cheeks! 💕 Perfect for that soft girl aesthetic or a fresh, everyday look.

text:
👧🥰 “Girl at Heart - Kaja Jelly Charm Lip & Blush Glazed Keychain Stain”

🍒 @kajabeauty The Kaja Jelly Charm Lip & Blush Glazed Keychain Stain (Cherry Spritz) is one of the products from my recent @sephora haul. 🛍️ I was drawn to it by its irresistible packaging and versatile color. I love how lightweight it feels, and it can be built up for a pop of jelly-like color on the lips and cheeks. 👄

💕 The love charm keychain is absolutely adorable, and the shade Cherry Spritz, a red with a blue undertone, helps enhance my skin complexion. I wouldn’t say it’s a long-lasting color, as I need to reapply several times a day, which doesn’t bother me. However, it might not be the best choice for those seeking a long-wearing lip stain.

🥰 When using it as a liquid blush, I prefer to apply it with my fingers, as it’s easier to control the color. For seamless blending, apply it on bare skin or over a product with a liquid or creamy texture. It’s weightless, making blending a breeze. 🍃

text:
💫 Products that actually work for acne and dull skin complexion! 🌟

Thanks to @axisy_official AXIS-Y for sending these goodies my way for an honest review. They arrived just in time as I was looking for brightening products to tackle my dull skin and excess sebum on my T-zone. Let’s dive in! 🌿💧

🌟 What is AXIS-Y Spot The Difference Blemish Treatment?
Formulated with 4-Terpineol, the active ingredient of tea tree leaf oil, it soothes and calms irritated skin. It also contains Heartleaf, Licorice Root Extract, and Pink Calamine Beads to control excess sebum and prevent breakouts. 🌿 The gentle formula is designed to be non-drying, making it perfect for sensitive, breakout-prone skin.

My Experience:
I use it around my nose to help control sebum, and I immediately feel a cooling sensation! 💙 It’s non-drying, and I love seeing the Pink Calamine Beads melt into my skin as I massage it in. 👃✨

💫 What is AXIS-Y Dark Spot Correcting Glow Serum?
Packed with Niacinamide (5%), a powerful ingredient that reduces hyperpigmentation and brightens dark spots. 💧 It also features Papaya Extract and Sea Buckthorn for skin regeneration, leaving your skin glowing and smooth. It’s perfect for fading dark spots and post-acne marks while giving the skin a bright and even complexion.

My Experience:
One of my faves — I’m on my second tube! 😍 It’s a holy grail for dull skin and post-acne marks, giving me a healthy, glowing finish without irritation or dryness. 🌟

☀️ What is AXIS-Y Complete No-Stress Physical Sunscreen V.3?
It contains Zinc Oxide, Niacinamide (2%) and Squalane, which hydrate the skin while soothing irritation.

My Experience:
💦 Its essence-gel-lotion texture layers perfectly over the Glow Serum, leaving just a subtle white sheen that actually brightens up my complexion. 💡🌞 I appreciate that it’s a physical sunscreen and doesn’t feel too thick or chalky on my skin. I would say it’s more suitable for dry skin, or oily and combination skin in dry weather. 🍁

Have you tried any of these? Let me know your thoughts! 💬👇

text:
~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this chemical sunscreen from Cetaphil today! 
🔆
- UV Filters: Avobenzone, Homosalate, Octisalate, and Octocrylene
- It has a cream texture
- No white cast on my skin tone
- No greyness in my facial hair
- Has a natural radiant finish
- No added fragrance and essential oils
- Stings my eyes
- Around 12-14 pumps to get the necessary amount for proper protection (around 1/2 teaspoon for face/neck)
- Around $15 for 88mL. Can be purchased from retailers like Target or CVS.

text:
Full scalp scare routine details ⤵️

I’ll begin by saying I’ve struggled with my scalp being very dry for a while and although my hair was growing it was also extremely dry, so I decided to shave my head and loved it, but the goal was to find products and a hair care routine that would give me a healthy scalp! 

I wasn’t even planing to grow my hair out and now I am after I stopped shaving 2 months ago. This is not a sponsored post nor were this products gifted, I spent my little coiiinnss @beyondbotanix okayyy. I just hope this helps the girlies who need it!

I like to start with the Fermented Herbal Onion Rice Water Treatment. I shake it well and then apply it to my scalp and hair. I massage and leave it on for 45 mins with a plastic cap, then I rinse out completely and keep it refrigerated! 

Then I follow up with the Cinnamon & Fenugreek Natural Scalp Scrub. I like to apply a good amount of scrub to my fingertips and then I begin massaging my entire scalp gently. I let it sit for about 10-15mins and rise out well.

Next I use the Aloe Vera and Clove Shampoo & Chebe and Neem Conditioner once a week routinely with the rest of my scalp/hair care routine.

Right after, I love spraying the Potent Herbal Scalp Tonic by applying it directly to the scalp and massaging. This is a leave in product!

Followed by the Moringa, Nettle & Ambunu Leave-In Conditioner which I use once a week. This one is best used on dry or damp hair, all you need to do is part your hair into sections and apply it to the scalp & hair.

Add a little extra moisturiser with the Herbal Citrus Rice Pudding Hair Spray. Shake it well, mist your scalp and hair every other day or as needed and don’t rinse out. 

I seal everything with the Herbal Hair Growth Oil. I like to use it everyday by applying to the scalp and massaging, but you can also use it as a hot oil treatment!

This is the scalp care or hair care routine that’s worked for me, but you can always feel free to leave out products you might not necessarily need depending on your hair type and scalp care needs.

Again, I just hope this helps the girlies that need it.

Happy #scalpcare & #haircare journey! 🎀

Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this new chemical sunscreen from Kiehl’s today! 
🔆
- UV Filters: Avobenzone, Homosalate, Octisalate, and Octocrylene
- It has a fluid lotion texture
- No white cast on my skin tone
- Works well in my facial hair
- Has a natural radiant finish
- Does not sting me eyes
- Around 10-12 pumps to get the necessary amount for proper protection (around 1/2 teaspoon for face/neck)
- No added fragrance or essential oils
- Around $42 for 50mL. Can be purchased from their website or credo beauty.
🔆
Love not having to spend like 2 minutes rubbing my face. No white cast or issues in my facial hair. Maybe those with super oily skin would not enjoy this, because it has me looking quite shiny at the end of the day from its moisture. But I think it can work for a variety of people. I don’t go to sunscreens for the added ingredients, but this does also have added peptides that are supposed to help with stimulating collagen production. Solid new launch! text:
*Cristiano Ronaldo: A Football Icon*

Cristiano Ronaldo, born on February 5, 1985, in Madeira, Portugal, is widely regarded as one of the greatest footballers of all time. From a young age, Ronaldo showcased his prodigious talent, which saw him joining Sporting CP before making a high-profile move to Manchester United in 2003. His time at Manchester United was marked by rapid development, where his dribbling, pace, and ability to score goals from any position made him a fan favorite. Ronaldo's impact at Old Trafford was profound, helping the club secure three Premier League titles, a UEFA Champions League, and a host of other honors. His 2008 Ballon d'Or win was the first of many accolades that would define his illustrious career.

#CristianoRonaldo #CR7 #ManchesterUnited #PremierLeague #FootballLegend #GOAT #BallondOr #Madeira #SportingCP #RedDevils #ChampionsLeague #SoccerStar #RonaldoMagic #FootballIcon

In 2009, Ronaldo made a world-record transfer to Real Madrid, where he would cement his legacy as one of the sport's greatest. His time at the Santiago Bernabéu was nothing short of legendary. Ronaldo scored an astonishing 450 goals in 438 appearances, becoming the club’s all-time leading scorer. His goal-scoring feats included an incredible consistency in the UEFA Champions League, where he led Real Madrid to four titles in five years. Ronaldo's rivalry with Lionel Messi during this period became one of the most talked-about aspects of football, with fans and pundits alike debating who was the better player.

#RealMadrid #HalaMadrid #LosBlancos #UCL #Galacticos #RonaldoVsMessi #FootballHistory #ChampionsLeagueFinal #AllTimeScorer #RonaldoGoals #ElClasico #SoccerGOAT #RonaldoVsMessi #SoccerKing

In 2018, Ronaldo sought a new challenge and transferred to Juventus in Serie A, where he continued to defy expectations. In Italy, Ronaldo maintained his extraordinary standards, leading Juventus to consecutive Serie A titles and further cementing his reputation as a goal-scoring machine. Despite being in his mid-30s, his physical prowess, dedication to training, and relentless pursuit of excellence ensured that he remained at the top of his game. Ronaldo's impact in Italy proved that his abilities transcended leagues and that he was capable of dominating in any environment.

#Juventus #SerieA #ForzaJuve #RonaldoJuventus #CR7Italy #ItalianFootball #GoalMachine #RonaldoFitness #SoccerLegend #RonaldoRecord #SerieATitles #JuveChampion #RonaldoInItaly #LegendContinues

Ronaldo's influence extends beyond the pitch as he has become a global icon and a brand in his own right. With millions of followers on social media, Ronaldo is one of the most marketable athletes in the world, endorsing major brands and launching his own CR7 product line. His work off the field, including charitable efforts and philanthropy, has further endeared him to fans around the globe. Ronaldo's ability to inspire young footballers and his contribution to the sport is immeasurable, solidifying his status as not just a footballer but a global phenomenon.

#CR7 #CristianoRonaldo #GlobalIcon #SoccerStar #RonaldoBrand #CR7Collection #RonaldoFans #FootballInspiration #RonaldoPhilanthropy #SoccerInfluence #RonaldoSocialMedia #RonaldoCharity #CR7Brand #WorldIcon

As of 2024, Ronaldo continues to play at the highest level, demonstrating an extraordinary longevity that few athletes can match. Whether it’s breaking records, scoring crucial goals, or simply inspiring the next generation of footballers, Ronaldo’s impact on the game remains unmatched. His journey from the streets of Madeira to becoming a global superstar is a testament to his hard work, talent, and unyielding determination. Ronaldo's legacy in football is secure, and his name will be remembered for generations as one of the sport's true greats.

#CR7Legacy #FootballGOAT #SoccerLegend #CristianoRonaldo #MadeiraToLegend #FootballHistory #RonaldoJourney #Longevity #GOATDebate #SoccerSuperstar #RonaldoInspiration #RonaldoRecords #GlobalLegend #CR7Forever

AMAZING HAIR RESTORATION IN JUST WEEKS
Hair loss is a deeply personal problem, affecting how you see yourself and how you face the world. For our patient, the struggle was all too real. As a woman experiencing significant hair thinning, she felt like she was losing more than just hair; she was losing confidence and her femininity. After trying countless products and seeing little to no change, she came to Ashley desperate for a solution that would finally work.

Ashley, our NYC-based nurse injector, worked closely with her to turn her hair loss into hair growth through advanced PRP therapy.  By injecting the platelet-rich plasma directly into the scalp, we delivered powerful growth factors that stimulate dormant hair follicles, essentially “jump-starting” their natural growth cycle. The addition of exosomes and stem cells supercharged the process, encouraging healthier, thicker, and stronger hair growth over time.

This patient’s transformation has been nothing short of remarkable. By targeting the root causes of hair loss and using cutting-edge regenerative techniques, Ashley helped her reclaim the confidence she thought was gone for good. It’s about more than just seeing hair grow back—it’s about seeing yourself in the mirror and feeling whole again. 

This is only after about a month! As more time passes, her hair will only continue to grow and thicken, so stay tuned for updates!

If you're grappling with hair loss and are tired of solutions that don't work, come see Ashley or myself to turn back the clock on your hair!

text:
Tower 28 launched three new shades of their OneLiner Lip Liners!

Description: A creamy, high-pigment, non-drying matte liner for lips, eyes, and cheeks to create infinite looks.

The Tower 28 OneLiners are one of my favorite lip liners of all time. The OG shade work of art is a tiny little stub in my makeup drawer and I already have a backup, so needless to say, I was STOKED when they launched three new shades.

These are just $15 and I’m always pleasantly surprised by Tower 28’s price point.

The formula has a great creaminess to it that allows the pencil to glide on like a dream, but there’s still grip to it so it doesn’t slide around or fade quickly. That said, if you want a budge-proof liner that sets down, this is not for you.

I can’t get enough of these and I love the new shades, I can’t even pick a favorite anymore. Work of Art, Check Me Out, and Paint My Number are all staples in my regular routine.

You can buy the Tower 28 OneLiners at Sephora: https://rstyle.me/+-xI-uIZODxhDH_OP55yGuQ

Step 1: Comb your brows into place with a spoolie

Step 4: Set the brows into place with a clear brow gel so they stay in place all day!

text:
Persona just launched two new shades of the Dreamstick Cream Blush today!

Carmel is a beautiful muted rose
Georgia is a gorgeous sun kissed peach

I usually don’t like cream blush for a variety of reasons: they never last well, they lift foundation, they’re sticky and hard to blend, and they’re often too dewy on my combination skin.

But I absolutely adore the Persona Dreamstick formula! The shade Bloom has been my favorite and now I think Carmel might be tied for #1! 

These are $26 and are an extremely bendable formula with a slight dewy finish, but it never feels sticky or greasy.  My face eats cream blush so it’s not the most long-lasting blush on me, but it performs better than 99% of cream blushes I’ve tried.

I’m so excited that Persona continues to expand their shade range of the Dreamstick!

Which shade do you like best?

Link to Dreamstick: https://rstyle.me/+G8bmxG7BQIdApD9BkhYGaQ

text:
How to get your lips to look like you’ve had them blushed without getting them blushed. 

Step 1: Use a lip liner to slightly over line your lips, I’m using medium pink rose from ‪@SmashboxCosmetics‬ 

Step 2: Apply a blush oil that reacts to your skin’s pH to give you the perfect shade, unique to you. I am the using BYO blush from ‪@youthforia‬ 

Step 3: Blend & clean up edges 

Step 4: Dab a little red lipstick (personally prefer a liquid lipstick) like this one “Bawse” from ‪@SmashboxCosmetics‬ and focus the color towards the center of your lips. 

Step 5: Let it dry & then use a tissue to bloat the excess lipstick off. Clean of edges if you need to. 

Step 6: Apply a gloss or lip oil of choice. I am using “Prestige” from Jule Lipgloss 

Step 7: Slay!!! And share this with someone who might need this quick beauty hack!!!

text:
Transforming complex acne scars requires expertise, precision, and a personalized approach—exactly what this patient sought when she traveled all the way across the country to see me. She’d been following my results on social media, amazed by the transformations she’d seen! For her, it wasn’t just about improving her skin- it was about reclaiming her confidence too.

Here’s the combination approach I used to target her deep ice pick and atrophic scars:

✅ Subcision - We began with subcision to break up the scar tissue bound to deeper layers of skin, creating new collagen formation and lifting indented areas

✅ Pixel - to gently resurface the outermost skin layers, improving overall texture and reducing the appearance of superficial scars. This step helped refine her skin for a smoother, more even finish.

✅ CO2 Laser - Finally, we used CO2 laser for deep remodeling. This powerful laser stimulates collagen production at a deeper level to support and lift the skin from within, especially beneficial for her more severe ice pick scars.

She's looking amazing just one month after her treatment! For best results, she'll be back for more maintenance and improvement. Every treatment plan is uniquely crafted to address your specific concerns and skin type, ensuring you get the most effective results with minimal downtime. With over 15 years of experience, I know how to create the perfect blend of treatments to help you achieve your skin goals.

Whether you’re looking to smooth out texture, diminish scars, or brighten your overall complexion, I’ll work with you to design a laser plan that truly fits your needs.

text:
CAMERA READY | SYLFIRM + MOXI 
Our patient is a television host who will be on camera in a week. In order to get his skin looking pristine and to achieve that youthful glow, he came to us for a dynamic duo combination treatment. This beloved treatment consist of Sylfirm and Moxi. @sylfirmx.usa uses micro needling radio frequency to work wonders by getting a balanced complexion, minimizing pores as well as fine lines and wrinkles, and treating skin laxity. We commonly use Sylfirm on the face and neck, however, it can truly be used ALL OVER the body to improve laxity anywhere. After Sylfirm, comes the “bright” aspect- Moxi. We love this laser as it combats signs of aging, improves and balances the skin’s tone and texture, plus when combined with Sylfirm it will achieve enhanced results leaving reduced skin laxity. Right after his treatment we began his after care- using the EMER SKIN Hydration Mask to soothe and calm his skin post micro needling and laser. To maximize his results, he used the EMER SKIN Dermergency Kit in the days following his treatment. Not only does the Dermergency Kit help with sun damage, but it minimizes pores and uneven skin tones. His skin is looking more youthful and radiant than ever- plus his complexion is now balanced. 

BENEFITS OF MOXI 
✅ Downtime is customized
✅ Safe for every skin type 
✅ Can be combined with MNRF to combat skin laxity
✅ Can be combined with BBL HERO for redness
✅ Add PRP to enhance improvement and speed healing
✅ Treatment greatly reduces the risk for skin cancer and 
✅ Treatment is effective in treating signs of skin aging such as rosacea, uneven pigmentation, tone, texture and fine lines

The DERMERGENCY KIT is designed to be used as a skin "booster" to help improve outbreaks, get you ready for an event, or just maintain your skin with a once or twice a month at-home treatment. Want to see how quickly his complexion improved?

text:
~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this new chemical sunscreen from Rovectin today! 
🔆
- UV Filters: Uvinul A Plus, Uvinul T 150, Parsol SLX, Tinosorb M
- It has a light cream texture
- No white cast on my skin tone
- Shows greyness in my facial hair
- Has a natural finish
- No added fragrance and essential oils
- Does not sting my eyes
- Around $22 for 50mL. Can be purchased from retailers like Stylevana or YesStyle. Code SHOPGSG for discount on Stylevana.
🔆
This is a new launch from the brand and I was excited to check it out because I feel like I haven't tried a new Korean sunscreen in a minute! Has that same standard great texture and application experience you can expect from a lot of Korean sunscreens. Although I didn't have any white cast, you might see something if you are darker than me and I wouldn't recommend it for those that have dark coarse facial hair like I do because of the Tinosorb M. But for everyone else, it's pretty nice. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
It cosmetics confidence in a gel cream

~PR~
As someone with oily skin, gel creams are always gonna have a special place in my heart lol. They really are the go-to. This new one from @itcosmetics is the perfect texture I love. It is a beautifully lightweight gel cream that is easy to apply.
⚡️
I've only been using it for a couple weeks, but it is deeply hydrating for my skin, which I appreciate. It has a good ingredient mix of Niacinamide, Peptides, and Zinc PCA. 
⚡️
It does minimize shine when it is applied, but I don't notice any real oil control throughout the day from it, so idk about that claim. The price is also higher than I would like for a moisturizer. But I do like it enough to continue use, so I'll update how I feel in a couple weeks.

#skincareroutine #gelcream #oilyskin #moisturizer #oilcontrol #mensskincare #mensselfcare #itcosmetics #giftedbyitcosmetics

text:
Live Tinted sent me their new blush crush, a tinted blush serum in four shades.

They’re $22 each and the website says they’re a “creamy liquid blush that easily blends and builds for naturally flushed, flirty cheeks that last all day.”

If you’re new here, my face says cream blush, so I figured these would work for me and I was right. They feel extremely oily and when I wore them on top of a matte foundation, they broke up my base and made a total mess.

When I tried them on top of a glowy foundation (like in this video) they didn’t break up my foundation, but they did look a little patchy, and they faded extremely fast.

I have combination skin so I personally don’t love a dewy cheek, but if you have dry skin or love a wet-finish, I could see you enjoying these.

*pr

Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this chemical sunscreen from Coppertone today! 
🔆
- UV Filters: Avobenzone, Homosalate, Octisalate, and Octocrylene
- It has a clear gel texture
- No white cast on my skin tone
- Works fine in my facial hair
- Has a radiant finish
- Has added fragrance but I don't find it strong
- Does not sting my eyes
- Water and sweat resistant
- Around $10 for 59mL. Can be purchased from their retailers like Target.
🔆
I believe this is new since I just saw it popping up in my stores. I just don't love the feel of this on my skin, so I still prefer other options for the clear gel sunscreens. It just kinda sits on top of my skin. This is pretty affordable, so decent enough to check out. I would just pass if you have oily skin. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
Pleasantly surprised by the new Saie slip tint concealer! (They sent me shades 4 and 5 in pr.)

At first, I didn’t like the way it looked because it’s so thin and blendable that the coverage blended away too quickly and it settled/creased easily. Plus, shade 5 is also too warm for me.

But after I set the concealer with powder and did the rest of my makeup, I noticed that it started to become more “one with my skin.” The formula worked really well with powder to prevent it from sliding around too much, and I like that it has a satin natural finish, it’s not too dewy but not too matte. That’s why a wear test is important, the formula grew on me as I wore it.

I’d say if you like medium coverage and you want a concealer that is super blendable and thin, that you can use all over the face or as under-eye concealer - this is for you.

If you’re like me and you prefer a more full coverage concealer with a tackier/thicker formula, or you have cool pink undertones, then I’d pass.

Note: I swatched all of the fair and light shades at Sephora and every shade looked yellow :/ unfortunately this is a pretty standard experience for me with clean beauty brands. Justice for cool tones!

Thanks to @axisy_official for sending me the Dark Spot Correcting Glow Serum and Vegan Collagen Eye Serum for reviews. Here’s a quick unboxing video and my first impression of the Glow Serum:

🌿 AXIS-Y Dark Spot Correcting Glow Serum contains 5% Niacinamide that improves dark spots and uneven skin tone. With the help of plant-derived Squalane, this serum retains moisture to keep the skin glowing and healthy.

My first impression:

💚 It’s a lightweight brightening serum in gel texture that is suitable for all skin types.

text:
My Experience with a Makeup Spatula and Fenty Beauty Matte Foundation 💄✨

I never thought I’d try a makeup spatula, but after watching tons of makeup videos on YouTube, I decided to give it a shot. I paired the spatula with the Fenty Beauty Pro Filt’r Soft Matte Longwear Foundation to see if this combination works well on my textured skin. The foundation is on the heavier side (medium to full coverage), so I believed the spatula would help thin it out, which is perfect for my combination skin and the humid weather in Hong Kong 💦🇭🇰.

My guess was right! The foundation looks more natural and is less likely to get patchy since there’s less product on my face to begin with. 🌟

How to use it:

🖐️ Place the foundation on the back of your hand or use a steel makeup palette like I do.
🎨 Glide the spatula with the foundation on your face, starting from the inside out.
💦 Wet the attached sponge to blend the foundation.

I had a lot of fun using it, but I don’t think I’ll use it daily as it takes more time to finish my makeup. Still, the tool looks great on my dressing table, and I’m happy I got it!

* The spatula I bought is by Shobido, which you can find on Amazon.

* Self-Purchased Item.

text:
❓What is it?
✅ This moisturizer combines Aloe Vera Extract for hydrating, soothing, protecting, and retaining water in the skin. It also contains Organic Grape Water which moisturises and soothes the skin without leaving a greasy layer.

According to the product website, this product is designed for normal to combination skin and it doesn’t have Parabens, Sulfates, Silicone, or other harmful ingredients.

On top of that, it is blended with
✅ 98% Natural Origin Ingredients
✅ Dermatologically Tested
✅ Non-Comedogenic and
✅ Vegan

Sounds great, right? But….

🤔 My POV: I have normal to dry skin and I do need an extra boost in Winter so this product is a bit too light for my skin type. I have been using this moisturizer in the morning for 2 weeks but my skin feels a bit tight so I need to mix it with another facial oil or use a serum before this moisturizer for extra skin nourishment. This is fine with me as I know my skin needs different products during the year; for example, AHA/BHA in Summer but facial oil or snail mucin essence in Winter, but what bothers me is the FRAGRANCE contained in the moisturizer.

😔 I don’t have sensitive skin so I don’t mind using a product with fragrance but this one is just too strong, too overwhelming, and too artificial!

Some reviews on their website say that this cream peels off and it doesn’t mix well with their makeup or sunscreen. I do not have this problem though as I use it with facial oil and blend it on the palm to warm up the product first, then massage it on the skin so the finish is soft and smooth. If you have a peeling problem when you use this product, you may use this way to prepare it before using it.

I really want to love this moisturizer but I don’t. 🙁 It’s a pity as I know the texture will be perfect for my skin type in Summer. Their “Clean for Skin” concept, “Non-irritating” and “Clean for Planet” formulas are what I appreciate but I just can’t deal with the heavy fragrance.

Is it only my thing? Will you use a skin care product with fragrance?

text:
SPECTACULAR SKINVIVE
Our patient today is a model, so naturally she wants to look her best on and off camera. She's noticed her skin has been dry, so to fix this she came in for one of our newest treatments: Skinvive. 

SKIN GLOW
Skinvive is very diverse- it can be used as a micro needling treatment, done in between laser treatments, as a combo treatment with a facial, or to hydrate the skin making it glow more than ever.

SMALL BUT MIGHTY
Consisting of hyaluronic acid, Skinvive has a gel-like texture and targets the skin superficially. Check out the little blebs- that's how we know her skin is getting that extra hydration.

INTERNAL CHAPSTICK
We meticulously treat all areas of her face, this will not only ensure her skin is completely hydrated- but also reduce any fine lines or wrinkles she has.

JAWLINE TIME
Moving onto the jawline, we do multiple passes along and under her jawline to tighten the skin in this area. One of the many reasons patients love this treatment is due to the minimal downtime, a couple days of healing for 6 months of glowing, hydrated skin- that's a no brainer.

LAST BUT NOT LEAST
We went the extra mile by treating her hairline, she did another treatment with us using an organic filler so this will maximize her results from both treatments. We love combination treatments and Skinvive is a perfect example of this.

IMMEDIATELY AFTER
She found the procedure to be slightly painful but overall not that bad and definitely worth it in the end.

DAY 2
She is a little swollen and has a small bruise but so far she is loving her results.

text:
🌵 Dry Skin Remedy - I’m from Rice Cream 🌾

After almost 2 weeks of travel, I feel like my skin needs an extra boost of hydration to soothe fine lines and soften my rough skin texture 😅 I’m from Rice Cream came at a perfect time when my skin needed the most attention 😘

I love using I’m from Rice Cream after the Rice Toner and the Rice Serum. The face cream offers intensive moisturization and rehydration to my skin. I love the glowy result and it seems that my fine lines have improved. 🥹 However, when the weather is getting warmer, I think the cream becomes a little bit too rich for me so I have switched my routine - from using it twice a day to once in the evening. 💕 I love how spreadable the cream is so I use it on my neck and collarbone as a massage cream too.

🌾 So what is I’m from Rice Cream?
1️⃣ It is a moisturizing cream infused with 41% Rice Bran Essence for skin barrier improvement and skin moisturization.
2️⃣ Blends with natural fatty acids which help to improve the skin barrier to protect the skin from environmental damage.
3️⃣ Fragrance-free and Artificial Coloring Free

Another interesting fact about this cream is how the company extracts the Rice Bran Essence. They claim that a Vacuum Distillation Extraction Method is used, in which the water is boiled at a low temperature with the Rice Bran and after 60 mins, the Rice Bran Essence is extracted and collected so it is not a synthetic skincare ingredient.

😄 My thoughts on this cream:
❤️ Great moisturization! If you have dry skin, this cream is for you!
❤️ Improves fine lines & dull skin complexion.
❤️ Smooths my rough skin texture.
❤️ Use it as a night or a massage cream if you have normal or normal to dry skin. Your skin will thank you for the softness and bounciness.
🤨 However, I do not recommend it for oily skin, and if you have sensitive eyes, avoid using it on eye areas.

I’ve tried countless eye creams, but Shiseido’s strikes the perfect balance. Its rich, velvety texture absorbs beautifully and layers seamlessly under makeup! 💫

For deep wrinkles and dark circles, it takes longer to see results, so I suggest using this eye cream day and night with a massage routine for better absorption and anti-wrinkle effects. 💆‍♀️✨

What is Shiseido Future Solution LX Eye and Lip Contour Regenerating Cream?

The Shiseido Future Solution LX Eye and Lip Contour Regenerating Cream is inspired by 40 years of genetic research. 🧬 It is specially formulated to improve the delicate areas around the eyes and lips 👁️👄. text:
♥️ The Only Foundation You Need - TirTir Mask Fit Red Cushion ♥️

I hate myself for not trying TirTir Cushion Foundation sooner and I have wasted so much money on other foundations 😔 but literally, this is the one I should have used a long time ago!

I bought a TirTir Mask Fit Red Cushion in 23N Sand at YesStyle. I thought it would be too dark for my skin tone but it turns out great! And don’t be fooled by the makeup puff when you pick up the foundation - a single press and you have enough for the whole face. You can see that I applied too much on half of my face but when I pressed the puff on the tissue and spread the foundation to the other half, it became perfect! 😍

⭐ POV: What do I think about the coverage?
✅ The coverage is great and it’s not too thick. It brightens my skin tone naturally and it won’t dry out my skin (I have normal to dry skin).

The product claims that it is smudge-proof and lasts for up to 72 hours! 🤔 I didn’t leave the foundation on my skin for that long but compared to other liquid foundations, it is more long-lasting and won’t be smudged even though I use facial tissue to press my cheeks during the day. Having said that, I do use loose powder to set my makeup, and the foundation is off a bit on my nose area due to sebum production. After all, my makeup still looks natural - not cakey, not dry and I LOVE it ❤️❤️❤️

⭐ Will I recommend it?
✅ Definitely Yes! 10/10 🌟 The product is great and it’s about US$25 - a very good deal when you compare other not-so-great cushion foundations. No wonder it became viral and I see it everywhere on social media 📺

text:
J-Beauty That Rivals High-End Products - Canmake Vs Valentino 🌸✨

Today, I’m comparing two amazing products: Canmake Cream Cheek in P05 Pale Lilac and Valentino Eye2Cheek Eyeshadow and Blush in 03 Rosa Emozione. Let’s dive in! 💕

💜 Canmake Cream Cheek P05 Pale Lilac: This beautiful pale lilac adds a soft, ethereal glow to your cheeks. The texture is powder to creamy, easy to blend, and leaves your skin glowy. It can be used as a highlighter as the pearly shimmer contained in the product is quite intense.

The powder is fine and smooth, which I love, but the packaging is basic and doesn’t come with an applicator brush.

💖 Valentino Eye2Cheek 03 Rosa Emozione: This luxurious blush doubles as an eyeshadow in a stunning rosy pink shade, with a touch of lavender and light-reflecting pearls. The texture is smooth and easy to blend, with a finely milled powder gliding effortlessly onto the skin.

The packaging is where Valentino truly shines—encased in the signature red and gold, it comes with an attached brush for convenient application. It’s a true statement piece on your vanity!

📝 My Experience:
Both products have a similar texture that’s easy to blend, and the powder is fine and smooth. Valentino has more pink to it, while Canmake has more purple. However, once they are applied to the skin, the colors look quite similar to me, though the shimmery result of Canmake is more obvious. ✨

In terms of packaging, Valentino’s luxurious design definitely stands out. However, the price difference of over $40 is significant. 💸💰

Which one will you choose? Let me know your thoughts! ✨

Canmake is available on YesStyle.com Use my code BEAUTYKAT321 for more savings!

~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this chemical sunscreen from Coola today! 
🔆
- UV Filters: Avobenzone, Homosalate, Octisalate, and Octocrylene
- It has a gel cream texture
- No white cast on my skin tone
- Works well in my body hair
- Has a natural finish
- Did sting my eyes at the end of the day
- Around 10 pumps to get the necessary amount for proper protection (around 1/2 teaspoon for face/neck)
- No added synthetic fragrance, but still has a scent from extracts
- Around $48 for 30mL. Can be purchased from their website.
🔆
I’ve liked the majority of their sunscreens that I’ve tried so far, so I’m always down to try a new one! I like the finish quite a bit, very natural. There's no synthetic fragrance added, but it does have a little bit of a scent to it. I guess from extracts and essential oils probably. My issue with this one is that it did sort of sting my eyes sometimes later on in the day. Also it is very pricey, especially considering it’s only 1 ounce. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
I really liked the Glossier lip line in Grip so I bought another shade, Bit.

Here are my thoughts:

This is for those of you who want a highly pigmented, budge-proof formula (which is not me.)

It worked for the shade grip because I loved it as an all-over-the-lips flush of warm pink, but as a lip liner I didn’t like it because the color was so bright.

Since Bit is described as a warm mauve, I thought it might be my perfect shade but it’s too deep for what I wanted, it’s ultra-pigmented, and it sets so fast that I don’t love the way it looks as a liner or all over the lips. It’s really impossible to smudge and it’s so dark that it just doesn’t look natural on me as a liner.

This is obviously just me being super picky but I wanted to share for those of you who are considering this shade.

Lip Line at Sephora: https://rstyle.me/+68s0-06RdejyfSFChORg2w

1.  The Ordinary.  is a fan favorite, known for its science-based, single-ingredient formulas like Niacinamide 10% + Zinc 1% and Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner. Their products often cost less than $10, making them a go-to for effective, low-cost skincare

2.  CeraVe.  is widely praised for its gentle yet effective formulations, especially their Hydrating Cleanser and Moisturizing Lotion, which are often recommended for sensitive or dry skin. Their products are budget-friendly and frequently recommended by dermatologists

3. The Inkey List.  is another affordable brand offering straightforward skincare solutions. Their Oat Cleansing Balm and Hyaluronic Acid Serum are standouts, priced around $10, designed to simplify routines without sacrificing results

4. e.l.f. Skincare. offers products like the Holy Hydration! Moisturizer, which is under $15 and well-reviewed for its hydrating benefits

5. *Weleda Skin Food* is a cult favorite, known for its ultra-rich moisturizing properties. It's especially popular for dry patches and as a makeup primer, with great reviews for its $13 price tag

text:
💧Laneige Water Bank Blue Hyaluronic Intensive Moisturizer💧
~PR~
They has this trio of moisturizers now, and I’ve already tried two of them, the gel and the cream, which got a little bit of changes to them. But this one here is completely new. This is the intensive moisturizer from the water bank hyaluronic acid line.
💧
I think it has pretty standard ingredients when it comes to hydration and moisture so nothing too special there. It does have an added Omega Peptide Complex to help fortify the skin's moisture barrier. I would say there is added fragrance to it. I think it’s a pleasant smell and not too apparent. But if you’re looking out for fragrance, you might want to skip this one.
💧
The interesting thing with this and the number one selling point in my opinion is the texture. It has a sort of thick, almost cream cheese, type of texture. I know that sounds crazy but if you’ve tried the L’Occitane hand cream, it’s a very similar texture to that one, you can almost squish it in your hand, which is really interesting. But once you rub it in your hand and it melts down, you apply it on the skin easily. It dries down very well and is not greasy on the skin. I love this as a night cream, considering I have oily skin.
💧
I feel like moisturizers of this texture are pretty hard to come by so it’s definitely nice to check out. Price-wise it’s decent. It’s in the Sephora price range. If you would check this one out for yourself let me know what you think.

#skincarereviews #laneige #newskincare #newlaunch #dryskin #hyaluronicacid #moisturizer

text:
I purchased the new Westman Atelier Lip Suede Matte Lipstick in the shade Je Rêve.

They’re $50 each and they are described as, “A hydrating matte lipstick with a dreamy, airy feel and vivid, clean pigment. Plump, nourish and smooth with a blend of peptides, Vitamins C, E, and Hydro Suede Technology: a volumizing, moisture-locking system that delivers matte pigment without drying or feathering.”

Packaging: Weighted, refillable packaging with a magnetic mirrored cap. It feels very luxurious, but heads up - it’s very bulky. Not practical for me to put in my purse.

Shade: Je Rêve is described as a blushy nude, which could be interpreted a million ways. On the website, the shade looks like a mauve, so when I applied it and saw how rosy red it turned, I was very disappointed. But that will depend on your unique skin tone.

My experience: To me, these are not worth $50. I had the same experience with the Mac powderkiss lipsticks, in that they have that creamy, powdery feel that glides on easily but ends up feeling dry on my lips. The Westman Atelier formula is much more thin and a bit more emollient than the Mac version, but that’s my closest comparison.

My friends have been loving this formula and said it wasn’t drying on them, so this is all subjective! For me to want to spend $50 on a lipstick, I need a moisturizing formula, a blurring effect, and a flattering shade.

Link to Lip Suede: https://rstyle.me/+H0FP6E6huxoHMPNNKiCLjA

text:
🥰 Fenty Beauty by Rihanna vs Armani Beauty 🥰

I bought these two foundations at Sephora because I always want to compare the finish of my favorite beauty brands. 😄

🧐 What is Fenty Beauty by Rihanna PRO FILT’R SOFT MATTE LONGWEAR FOUNDATION?

This is a buildable, medium to full coverage foundation that is designed to combat heat, sweat, and shine.

✅ My Thoughts on Fenty Beauty: this is a nice semi-matte foundation that covers my large pores and light pigmentation. It’s a bit thick so I have to use a foundation blender to apply it which makes the whole application process much easier.

🧐 What is Armani Beauty Luminous Silk Perfect Glow Flawless Oil-Free Foundation?

This is an oil-free liquid foundation that provides light to medium coverage and a luminous finish for a natural makeup look.

✅ My Thoughts on Armani Beauty: this is my all-time favorite, if I don’t consider the price, as the coverage is light and buildable. It spreads easily on my skin, so if I’m in a rush, I’ll simply use my fingers to apply the foundation. It gives me a natural finish and makes my skin glow.

🥰 Fenty Beauty by Rihanna vs Armani Beauty 🥰:

For a light to medium daily foundation without worrying about the price ($69 for 30ml), choose Armani Beauty.

For medium to full coverage that lasts all day long, Fenty Beauty is your choice ($40 for 32ml).

My favorite is still Armani Beauty ❤️. I love the weightless finish and subtle glow it provides. I do need to touch up with powder foundation when the weather is humid, but I don’t mind at all.

Having said that, Fenty Beauty has just launched a luminous foundation with hydrating ingredients, so I may change my mind later. 🤯

4. Weleda Plumping Facial Oil: A lightweight facial oil that absorbs quickly and gives your skin a beautiful, hydrated glow. It's perfect for those who want to avoid scrubbing and harsh exfoliants.

5. Sofie Pavitt Mandelic Clearing Serum ($54): This gentle serum helps to clear and brighten the skin without irritation, perfect for a smooth, glowing complexion without physical exfoliation.
These products focus on hydration, brightening, and skin repair, giving you that glowing, radiant skin without the need for scrubbing or harsh exfoliants.

My all-time favorite lip product, the Nature Republic Honey Melting Lip Balms now comes in 5 new shades! And they’re launching an ultra sheer pink and black soon as well!

If you haven’t tried this formula, it’s super thick and nourishing, has great grip, an apricot scent, medium pigment, and an ultra-smoothing, glass-like shine.

This new collection definitely has less pigmented than the initial 5 shades, which is a bummer, but they’re still beautiful. You can see on the arm swatches that some of the shades look almost identical in this collection so I don’t think you need all 5.

My favorite shades are fig, berry, lychee, and black cherry.
